1
00:00:28,612 --> 00:00:30,477
[HISSES]

2
00:00:32,616 --> 00:00:36,404
[SPEAKING IN PARSELTONGUE]

3
00:01:26,670 --> 00:01:28,752
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER RADIO]

4
00:01:48,025 --> 00:01:50,437
Bloody kids.

5
00:02:36,907 --> 00:02:40,570
MAN: How fastidious you’ve become,
Wormtail.

6
00:02:40,744 --> 00:02:45,113
As I recall, you once called
the nearest gutter pipe home.

7
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:47,201
Could it be that the task of nursing me...

8
00:02:47,376 --> 00:02:48,411
[STAIR CREAKS]

9
00:02:48,627 --> 00:02:50,492
...has become wearisome for you?

10
00:02:50,671 --> 00:02:53,128
Oh, no. No, no, my Lord Voldemort.

11
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:54,580
I only meant...

12
00:02:54,758 --> 00:02:57,716
...perhaps if we were to do it
without the boy.

13
00:02:57,886 --> 00:03:00,252
No! The boy is everything!

14
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:03,968
It cannot be done without him.
And it will be done.

15
00:03:04,142 --> 00:03:06,804
Exactly as I said.

16
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:10,933
-I will not disappoint you, my Lord.
VOLDEMORT: Good.

17
00:03:11,108 --> 00:03:14,145
First, gather our old comrades.

18
00:03:14,319 --> 00:03:16,560
Send them a sign.

19
00:03:21,201 --> 00:03:24,284
[SNAKE SPEAKS IN PARSELTONGUE]

20
00:03:28,291 --> 00:03:31,783
VOLDEMORT: Nagini tells me
the old Muggle caretaker...

21
00:03:31,962 --> 00:03:35,625
...is standing just outside the door.

22
00:03:35,799 --> 00:03:41,135
Step aside, Wormtail, so I can give
our guest a proper greeting.

23
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:43,135
<i>Avada Kedavra!</i>

24
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:46,222
[FRANK YELLING]
[KETTLE WHISTLING]

25
00:03:48,145 --> 00:03:49,635
HERMIONE: Harry.
-Ah!

26
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:52,058
Harry!

27
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:55,144
Are you all right?

28
00:03:55,861 --> 00:03:57,977
Hermione. Bad dream.

29
00:03:58,155 --> 00:04:01,488
-When did you get here?
-Just now. You?

30
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:02,898
Last night.

31
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:05,317
Wake up! Wake up, Ronald!

32
00:04:05,495 --> 00:04:06,735
Bloody hell.

33
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:08,403
Honestly, get dressed.

34
00:04:09,166 --> 00:04:10,906
And don't go back to sleep.

35
00:04:11,084 --> 00:04:14,417
Come on, Ron!
Your mother says breakfast's ready!

36
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:22,675
HARRY:
Ron, where are we actually going?

37
00:04:22,846 --> 00:04:23,926
RON:
Don't know.

38
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:27,677
-Hey, Dad. Where are we going?
-Haven't the foggiest.

39
00:04:27,851 --> 00:04:29,341
Keep up!

40
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,769
MAN:
Arthur!

41
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:35,931
It's about time, son.

42
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:40,478
Sorry, Amos. Some of us
had a bit of a sleepy start.

43
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:43,146
This is Amos Diggory, everyone.

44
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:46,317
Works with me at the Ministry.

45
00:04:46,787 --> 00:04:49,028
And this strapping young lad
must be Cedric, am I right?

46
00:04:49,206 --> 00:04:50,366
Yes, sir.

47
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,201
This way.

48
00:04:53,919 --> 00:04:57,286
Merlin's beard!
You must be Harry Potter.

49
00:04:57,464 --> 00:05:00,206
-Yes, sir.
-Great, great pleasure.

50
00:05:00,383 --> 00:05:02,169
Pleasure to meet you too, sir.

51
00:05:04,805 --> 00:05:07,467
AMOS:
Yes, it's just over there.

52
00:05:09,726 --> 00:05:11,557
ARTHUR: Shall we?
AMOS: Oh, yeah.

53
00:05:11,728 --> 00:05:13,059
ARTHUR:
We don't want to be late.

54
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:17,223
AMOS: Come on. Nearly there now.
Get yourself into a good position.

55
00:05:18,235 --> 00:05:20,567
Why are they all standing around
that manky old boot?

56
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:23,228
-That isn't just any manky old boot.
-It's a Portkey.

57
00:05:23,406 --> 00:05:24,737
AMOS:
Time to go!

58
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:26,523
What's a Portkey?

59
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:30,740
-Ready! After three. One, two...
-Harry!

60
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:31,994
...three!

61
00:05:32,374 --> 00:05:35,662
[ALL YELLING]

62
00:05:43,051 --> 00:05:44,166
Let go, kids!

63
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:46,380
-What?!
ARTHUR: Let go!

64
00:05:46,555 --> 00:05:48,341
[KIDS YELLING]

65
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:53,175
[GRUNTING]

66
00:05:58,984 --> 00:06:01,566
I'll bet that cleared your sinuses, eh?

67
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:05,103
AMOS: Total shambles, as per usual.
-Thanks.

68
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:13,028
ARTHUR:
Go on, look at that!

69
00:06:13,290 --> 00:06:17,784
Well, kids, welcome to
the Quidditch World Cup!

70
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:23,459
ARTHUR:
Stay together! Keep up, girls!

71
00:06:24,968 --> 00:06:26,253
Look!

72
00:06:27,137 --> 00:06:29,423
ARTHUR:
Come on! Keep up, girls!

73
00:06:32,851 --> 00:06:34,762
Whoa!

74
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:37,719
-Aah!
-Blimey!

75
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:39,763
Parting of the ways, I think, old chap.

76
00:06:39,941 --> 00:06:41,306
-See you at the match.
-See you.

77
00:06:41,484 --> 00:06:42,815
-Cedric.
-Ced, come on.

78
00:06:42,986 --> 00:06:44,647
FRED:
See you later, Cedric.

79
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:46,902
Ah.

80
00:06:49,284 --> 00:06:51,366
Home sweet home.

81
00:06:53,163 --> 00:06:54,699
HARRY:
What?

82
00:07:01,922 --> 00:07:04,004
ARTHUR: Excellent, excellent.
HERMIONE: Ginny, look!

83
00:07:04,174 --> 00:07:05,755
ARTHUR: All to the bath.
HERMIONE: Look.

84
00:07:05,926 --> 00:07:08,167
Girls, choose a bunk and unpack.

85
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:11,174
Ron, get out of the kitchen.
We're all hungry.

86
00:07:11,348 --> 00:07:12,929
FRED AND GEORGE:
Get out of the kitchen!

87
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:16,307
-Feet off the table!
FRED AND GEORGE: Feet off the table!

88
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,681
I love magic.

89
00:07:35,038 --> 00:07:38,405
VENDOR: Get your Quidditch World Cup
programs here!

90
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:41,871
Blimey, Dad. How far up are we?

91
00:07:42,045 --> 00:07:43,455
LUCIUS:
Well, put it this way:

92
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:45,419
If it rains...

93
00:07:45,590 --> 00:07:47,922
...you'll be the first to know.

94
00:07:48,718 --> 00:07:51,084
Father and I are in
the minister's box...

95
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:54,550
...by personal invitation
of Cornelius Fudge himself.

96
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:56,885
Don't boast, Draco.

97
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:59,176
There's no need with these people.

98
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:04,139
Do enjoy yourself, won't you?

99
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,398
While you can.

100
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:14,775
Yeah! Yeah!

101
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:21,747
AMOS:
Come on up. Take your seats.

102
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:24,455
I told you these seats
would be worth waiting for.

103
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:26,494
Come on!

104
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:30,714
FRED:
It's the Irish! There's Troy!

105
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:32,716
GEORGE: And Mullet!
FRED: And Moran!

106
00:08:38,393 --> 00:08:41,260
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Ireland! Ireland! Ireland!</i>

107
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:48,733
GEORGE: Here come the Bulgarians!
FRED: Yes!

108
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:50,234
ALL:
Whoa!

109
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:56,149
GINNY:
Who's that?

110
00:08:56,953 --> 00:08:59,945
That, sis, is the best Seeker
in the world.

111
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,538
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Krum! Krum! Krum!</i>

112
00:09:10,175 --> 00:09:11,506
HARRY, RON, FRED AND GEORGE:
Krum!

113
00:09:11,676 --> 00:09:14,088
-Yes!
-Whoo!

114
00:09:21,144 --> 00:09:23,055
Good evening!

115
00:09:23,605 --> 00:09:26,597
As Minister for Magic...

116
00:09:26,816 --> 00:09:29,853
...it gives me great pleasure...

117
00:09:30,487 --> 00:09:34,230
...to welcome
each and every one of you...

118
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:40,277
...to the final
of the 422nd Quidditch World Cup!

119
00:09:40,914 --> 00:09:42,279
Let the match...

120
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:44,246
...begin!

121
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,499
[CHEERING]

122
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:52,542
RON AND HARRY CHANTING:
<i>Krum! Krum! Krum!</i>

123
00:09:54,803 --> 00:09:58,216
[FRED AND GEORGE
SINGING GIBBERISH]

124
00:10:00,391 --> 00:10:02,052
There's no one like Krum.

125
00:10:02,227 --> 00:10:03,842
FRED: Krum?
-Dumb Krum?

126
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:07,057
He's like a bird,
the way he rides the wind.

127
00:10:07,232 --> 00:10:10,144
-He's more than an athlete.
-Dumb Krum.

128
00:10:10,318 --> 00:10:11,683
He's an artist.

129
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:14,022
-I think you're in love, Ron.
RON: Shut up.

130
00:10:14,239 --> 00:10:15,695
[SINGING]
<i>Viktor, I love you</>

131
00:10:15,865 --> 00:10:17,480
<i>Viktor, I do</i>

132
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:20,116
<i>When we're apart
My heart beats only for you</i>

133
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:21,321
[EXPLOSIONS]

134
00:10:21,496 --> 00:10:23,703
Sounds like the Irish
have got their pride on.

135
00:10:23,873 --> 00:10:25,613
ARTHUR:
Stop! Stop it!

136
00:10:26,167 --> 00:10:27,748
It's not the Irish.

137
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:31,039
We've gotta get out of here. Now!

138
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:32,996
[SCREAMING]

139
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:35,540
MAN:
Get out, it's the Death Eaters!

140
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:39,051
Get back to the Portkey, everybody,
and stick together!

141
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:41,884
Fred, George!
Ginny is your responsibility.

142
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:44,219
Go!

143
00:10:44,394 --> 00:10:46,225
Harry!

144
00:10:50,066 --> 00:10:51,977
[DEATH EATERS
CHANTING INDISTINCTLY]

145
00:11:01,035 --> 00:11:03,196
GEORGE: Keep up, you lot!
-Harry!

146
00:11:04,455 --> 00:11:06,571
Harry! Harry!

147
00:11:18,011 --> 00:11:20,172
[PANTING AND GRUNTING]

148
00:11:54,255 --> 00:11:55,745
<i>Morsmordre!</i>

149
00:12:22,492 --> 00:12:23,982
RON:
Harry!

150
00:12:25,495 --> 00:12:28,703
-Where are you?
HERMIONE: Harry!

151
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,574
RON:
We've been looking for you for ages!

152
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:35,501
Thought we lost you, mate.

153
00:12:36,339 --> 00:12:38,330
HARRY:
What is that?

154
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:40,252
[GROANS]

155
00:12:41,427 --> 00:12:43,509
WIZARDS:
<i>Stupefy!</i>

156
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:45,011
ARTHUR:
Stop!

157
00:12:45,181 --> 00:12:47,388
That's my son!

158
00:12:48,434 --> 00:12:51,096
-Ron, Harry, Hermione, you all right?
-We came back for Harry.

159
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:52,556
Which of you conjured it?

160
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:54,937
-Crouch, you can't possi--
-Do not lie!

161
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:57,099
You've been discovered
at the scene of the crime.

162
00:12:57,277 --> 00:12:59,268
-Crime?
-Barty! They're just kids.

163
00:12:59,445 --> 00:13:00,935
What crime?

164
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:03,605
It's the Dark Mark, Harry.
It's his mark.

165
00:13:03,783 --> 00:13:04,943
What, Voldemort?

166
00:13:06,119 --> 00:13:09,987
Those people tonight, in the masks,
they're his too, aren't they?

167
00:13:10,164 --> 00:13:12,371
-His followers?
-Yeah.

168
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,448
Death Eaters.

169
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:19,204
-Follow me.
-There was a man, before.

170
00:13:19,716 --> 00:13:21,047
There!

171
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:23,549
All of you, this way!

172
00:13:24,262 --> 00:13:25,718
ARTHUR:
A man, Harry?

173
00:13:26,014 --> 00:13:27,470
Who?

174
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,676
I don't know.

175
00:13:31,311 --> 00:13:33,518
I didn't see his face.

176
00:13:41,154 --> 00:13:43,236
[HISSING]

177
00:13:49,746 --> 00:13:51,737
WOMAN:
Anything from the trolley?

178
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:56,992
Anything from the trolley?

179
00:14:00,923 --> 00:14:02,663
Anything from the trolley, dears?

180
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:05,049
RON:
Packet of Drooble's...

181
00:14:05,219 --> 00:14:07,005
...and a Licorice Wand.

182
00:14:08,473 --> 00:14:10,555
On second thought, just the Drooble's.

183
00:14:10,725 --> 00:14:14,718
-It's all right, I'll get it. Don't worry.
-Just the Drooble's. Thanks.

184
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,392
Two Pumpkin Pasties, please.

185
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,395
Thank you.

186
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:28,239
WOMAN:
Anything sweet for you, dear?

187
00:14:29,077 --> 00:14:31,409
Oh, no, I'm not hungry. Thank you.

188
00:14:32,330 --> 00:14:34,321
WOMAN:
Anything from the trolley?

189
00:14:34,499 --> 00:14:36,535
HERMIONE:
This is horrible.

190
00:14:36,918 --> 00:14:39,625
How can the Ministry
not know who conjured it?

191
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:41,577
Wasn't there any security or...?

192
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:44,543
Loads, according to Dad.

193
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:48,676
That's what worried them so much.
Happened right under their noses.

194
00:14:51,307 --> 00:14:54,720
It's hurting again, isn't it?
Your scar.

195
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,555
I'm fine.

196
00:14:58,606 --> 00:15:01,473
You know Sirius will
want to hear about this...

197
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:05,644
...what you saw at the World Cup
and the dream.

198
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:17,288
Hedwig. There we go.

199
00:15:38,980 --> 00:15:42,598
[WHINNYING]

200
00:15:42,817 --> 00:15:46,401
[CHATTERING]

201
00:15:56,456 --> 00:15:58,742
Clear the runway!

202
00:16:01,669 --> 00:16:04,001
-Aah!
ALL: Whoa!

203
00:16:04,172 --> 00:16:06,914
Well, there's something
you don't see every day.

204
00:16:30,907 --> 00:16:33,364
DUMBLEDORE: Well, now we’re all
settled in and sorted...

205
00:16:33,534 --> 00:16:35,820
...I'd like to make an announcement.

206
00:16:36,829 --> 00:16:40,242
This castle will not only be
your home this year...

207
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:43,579
...but home to some
very special guests as well.

208
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:46,502
You see, Hogwarts has been chosen....

209
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:48,997
Yes, what is it?

210
00:16:49,217 --> 00:16:50,582
What is it?

211
00:16:50,760 --> 00:16:52,716
[WHISPERING]

212
00:16:52,929 --> 00:16:56,262
Tell them to wait.
Tell them to wait. Wait.

213
00:16:56,432 --> 00:17:02,393
So Hogwarts has been chosen
to host a legendary event:

214
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:04,599
The Triwizard Tournament.

215
00:17:05,066 --> 00:17:07,227
-For those of you who do not know...
BOTH: Brilliant.

216
00:17:07,401 --> 00:17:10,564
...the Triwizard Tournament
brings together three schools...

217
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,854
...for a series of magical contests.

218
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:16,490
From each school, a single student
is selected to compete.

219
00:17:16,744 --> 00:17:18,450
Now let me be clear.

220
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:21,533
If chosen, you stand alone.

221
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:23,618
And trust me when I say...

222
00:17:23,793 --> 00:17:26,785
...these contests are not
for the faint-hearted.

223
00:17:27,088 --> 00:17:31,422
But more of that later.
For now, please join me in welcoming...

224
00:17:31,592 --> 00:17:33,958
...the lovely ladies of the
Beauxbatons Academy of Magic...

225
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:35,588
[DOORS OPEN]

226
00:17:35,763 --> 00:17:39,756
...and their headmistress,
Madame Maxime.

227
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,806
[SIGHING]

228
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,857
RON:
Bloody hell.

229
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:04,079
Blimey. That's one big woman.

230
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,187
And now our friends from the north.

231
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:31,190
Please greet the proud sons
of Durmstrang...

232
00:18:31,360 --> 00:18:34,147
...and their high master,
Igor Karkaroff.

233
00:18:37,033 --> 00:18:39,069
[GRUNTING]

234
00:18:57,219 --> 00:18:58,800
STUDENT:
Oh, it's Krum!

235
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:00,427
Blimey, it's him!

236
00:19:00,598 --> 00:19:02,463
Viktor Krum!

237
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,810
KARKAROFF:
Albus.

238
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:14,691
Igor.

239
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:16,977
[THUNDER ROLLING]

240
00:19:28,334 --> 00:19:31,997
Professor Dumbly-dorr,
my horses have traveled a long way.

241
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:34,708
-They will need attending to.
-Don't worry, Madame Maxime.

242
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:38,420
Our gamekeeper, Hagrid,
is more than capable of seeing to them.

243
00:19:38,594 --> 00:19:40,835
MAXIME:
But you know, Monsieur Hagrid...

244
00:19:41,347 --> 00:19:43,633
...they drink only single-malt whiskey.

245
00:19:44,934 --> 00:19:46,299
Ah!

246
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:51,600
You idiot!

247
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:58,603
DUMBLEDORE:
Your attention, please!

248
00:20:00,991 --> 00:20:03,107
I'd like to say a few words.

249
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:06,906
Eternal glory.

250
00:20:07,373 --> 00:20:11,412
That is what awaits the student
who wins the Triwizard Tournament.

251
00:20:11,585 --> 00:20:15,794
But to do this, that student
must survive three tasks.

252
00:20:15,965 --> 00:20:19,833
Three extremely dangerous tasks.

253
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:22,710
BOTH: Wicked.
DUMBLEDORE: For this reason...

254
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:25,755
...the Ministry has seen fit
to impose a new rule.

255
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,298
To explain all this...

256
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:31,094
...we have the head of the Department
of International Magical Cooperation...

257
00:20:31,272 --> 00:20:33,388
...Mr. Bartemius Crouch.

258
00:20:34,775 --> 00:20:37,016
[THUNDER CRASHING]

259
00:20:39,697 --> 00:20:41,733
[SCREAMING]

260
00:20:47,830 --> 00:20:50,537
RON:
Bloody hell. It's Mad-Eye Moody.

261
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,541
-Alastor Moody? The Auror?
-Auror?

262
00:20:54,712 --> 00:20:58,170
Dark-wizard catcher. Half the cells
in Azkaban are filled thanks to him.

263
00:20:58,883 --> 00:21:02,000
He's supposed to be mad as a hatter,
though, these days.

264
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:07,508
[GRUNTING]

265
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:17,516
-My dear old friend, thanks for coming.
-Stupid ceiling.

266
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:18,808
Thank you.

267
00:21:25,326 --> 00:21:27,191
What's that he's drinking,
do you suppose?

268
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:30,612
I don't know, but I don't think
it's pumpkin juice.

269
00:21:37,588 --> 00:21:39,544
CROUCH:
After due consideration...

270
00:21:39,715 --> 00:21:42,582
...the Ministry has concluded that,
for their own safety...

271
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:45,718
...no student under the age of 17...

272
00:21:45,888 --> 00:21:49,631
...shall be allowed to put forth their
name for the Triwizard Tournament.

273
00:21:49,809 --> 00:21:52,516
-This decision is final.
FRED: That's rubbish!

274
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:55,268
That's rubbish!
You don't know what you're doing!

275
00:21:55,439 --> 00:21:59,182
-Silence!
-They're not too happy about that, then.

276
00:22:18,587 --> 00:22:20,999
The Goblet of Fire.

277
00:22:21,590 --> 00:22:24,457
Anyone wishing to submit themselves
to the tournament...

278
00:22:24,635 --> 00:22:27,547
...need only write their name
upon a piece of parchment...

279
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:30,804
...and throw it in the flame before
this hour on Thursday night.

280
00:22:31,934 --> 00:22:34,141
Do not do so lightly.

281
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:38,104
If chosen, there's no turning back.

282
00:22:38,274 --> 00:22:43,234
As from this moment,
the Triwizard Tournament has begun.

283
00:22:46,949 --> 00:22:50,066
[SHIP CREAKING]

284
00:22:58,168 --> 00:23:00,159
[DOOR SQUEAKS]

285
00:23:09,513 --> 00:23:11,469
Alastor Moody.

286
00:23:13,392 --> 00:23:15,007
Ex-Auror...

287
00:23:16,729 --> 00:23:19,141
...Ministry malcontent...

288
00:23:19,356 --> 00:23:21,768
...and your new
Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher.

289
00:23:21,942 --> 00:23:26,402
I am here because Dumbledore asked me.
End of story, goodbye, the end.

290
00:23:26,572 --> 00:23:28,312
Any questions?

291
00:23:31,493 --> 00:23:33,233
When it comes to the Dark Arts...

292
00:23:34,622 --> 00:23:37,284
...I believe in a practical approach.

293
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:43,169
But first, which of you can tell me
how many Unforgivable Curses there are?

294
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:46,004
-Three, sir.
-And they are so named?

295
00:23:46,175 --> 00:23:49,417
Because they are unforgivable.
The use of any one of them will--

296
00:23:49,595 --> 00:23:53,679
Will earn you a one-way ticket
to Azkaban, correct.

297
00:23:53,891 --> 00:23:56,633
The Ministry says you're too young
to see what these curses do.

298
00:23:56,810 --> 00:24:00,268
I say different! You need to know
what you're up against!

299
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:02,600
You need to be prepared.

300
00:24:02,775 --> 00:24:05,232
You need to find another place
to put your chewing gum...

301
00:24:05,402 --> 00:24:07,688
...besides the underside of your desk,
Mr. Finnigan!

302
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:10,855
No way. The old codger
can see out the back of his head.

303
00:24:11,575 --> 00:24:13,315
MOODY:
And hear across classrooms!

304
00:24:15,704 --> 00:24:19,196
So which curse shall we see first?

305
00:24:19,375 --> 00:24:20,581
-Weasley!
-Yes?

306
00:24:20,751 --> 00:24:22,082
Stand.

307
00:24:25,255 --> 00:24:27,041
Give us a curse.

308
00:24:27,216 --> 00:24:31,050
Well, my dad did tell me about one.

309
00:24:31,637 --> 00:24:32,877
The Imperius Curse.

310
00:24:33,055 --> 00:24:36,297
Oh, yeah, your father
would know all about that.

311
00:24:36,767 --> 00:24:39,429
Gave the Ministry quite a bit of grief
a few years ago.

312
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:42,386
Perhaps this will show you why.

313
00:24:48,362 --> 00:24:49,818
[INSECTS BUZZING]

314
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,361
Hello.

315
00:24:52,992 --> 00:24:54,698
Lovely little beauty.

316
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:56,483
[CHITTERING]

317
00:24:57,830 --> 00:24:59,821
<i>Engorgio.</i>

318
00:25:00,207 --> 00:25:01,868
<i>Imperio!</i>

319
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:04,833
[GASPING AND LAUGHING]

320
00:25:06,255 --> 00:25:08,712
MOODY:
Don't worry. It's completely harmless.

321
00:25:14,888 --> 00:25:16,549
If she bites...

322
00:25:17,099 --> 00:25:18,589
...she's lethal.

323
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:20,928
[DRACO CACKLING]

324
00:25:21,103 --> 00:25:22,934
What are you laughing at?

325
00:25:24,273 --> 00:25:25,683
Get off!

326
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:29,896
Talented, isn't she?

327
00:25:30,070 --> 00:25:33,437
What should I have her do next?
Jump out the window?

328
00:25:35,451 --> 00:25:36,816
Drown herself?

329
00:25:48,630 --> 00:25:51,872
Scores of witches and wizards
have claimed...

330
00:25:52,051 --> 00:25:56,044
...that they only did
You-Know-Who's bidding...

331
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:58,462
...under the influence
of the Imperius Curse.

332
00:25:58,640 --> 00:26:00,551
But here's the rub:

333
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:03,885
How do we sort out the liars?

334
00:26:06,231 --> 00:26:07,937
Another, another.

335
00:26:08,942 --> 00:26:10,478
Up, up. Come on.

336
00:26:10,652 --> 00:26:12,188
Longbottom, is it?

337
00:26:12,863 --> 00:26:14,353
Up.

338
00:26:16,408 --> 00:26:20,196
Professor Sprout tells me
you have an aptitude for herbology.

339
00:26:22,164 --> 00:26:23,825
There's the....

340
00:26:24,041 --> 00:26:25,997
The Cruciatus Curse.

341
00:26:26,168 --> 00:26:29,001
Correct, correct. Come, come.

342
00:26:29,213 --> 00:26:30,828
Particularly nasty.

343
00:26:33,884 --> 00:26:35,715
The torture curse.

344
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,085
<i>Crucio!</i>

345
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:40,504
[SQUEALING]

346
00:26:51,610 --> 00:26:55,398
Stop it! Can't you see
it's bothering him? Stop it!

347
00:27:07,167 --> 00:27:09,328
Um....

348
00:27:13,048 --> 00:27:17,041
Perhaps you could give us the last
Unforgivable Curse, Miss Granger.

349
00:27:19,471 --> 00:27:20,802
No?

350
00:27:22,015 --> 00:27:24,131
<i>Avada Kedavra!</i>

351
00:27:27,896 --> 00:27:29,432
The Killing Curse.

352
00:27:30,566 --> 00:27:33,729
Only one person is known
to have survived it...

353
00:27:34,278 --> 00:27:36,644
...and he's sitting in this room.

354
00:27:57,342 --> 00:28:00,459
[BELL TOLLING]

355
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:10,010
RON:
Brilliant, isn't he?

356
00:28:10,189 --> 00:28:14,228
Completely demented, of course, and
terrifying to be in the same room with...

357
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:17,564
...but he's really been there, you know?
He's looked evil in the eye.

358
00:28:17,738 --> 00:28:20,320
There's a reason those curses
are unforgivable.

359
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:24,654
To perform them in a classroom....
I mean, did you see Neville's face?

360
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:28,995
Neville?

361
00:28:29,166 --> 00:28:30,622
Son?

362
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:32,620
You all right?

363
00:28:33,587 --> 00:28:36,954
Come on. We'll have a cup of tea.
I want to show you something.

364
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:53,471
GIRL:
We're gonna be late!

365
00:28:59,738 --> 00:29:01,444
[CHATTERING]

366
00:29:04,034 --> 00:29:06,400
[APPLAUSE]

367
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:09,411
Come on, Cedric. Put it in!

368
00:29:15,712 --> 00:29:17,498
[APPLAUSE]

369
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:27,504
Eternal glory. Be brilliant, wouldn't it?

370
00:29:27,683 --> 00:29:30,345
Three years from now,
when we're old enough to be chosen.

371
00:29:30,519 --> 00:29:32,134
Yeah, rather you than me.

372
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:34,223
FRED AND GEORGE:
Yes!

373
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,352
Thank you, thank you.

374
00:29:38,527 --> 00:29:41,564
-Well, lads, we've done it.
-Cooked it up just this morning.

375
00:29:41,738 --> 00:29:43,899
It's not going to work.

376
00:29:45,117 --> 00:29:47,608
-Oh, yeah?
-And why is that, Granger?

377
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:50,744
You see this? This is an Age Line.

378
00:29:50,914 --> 00:29:52,700
Dumbledore drew it himself.

379
00:29:52,874 --> 00:29:54,330
So?

380
00:29:55,919 --> 00:29:59,537
So a genius like Dumbledore
couldn't possibly be fooled...

381
00:29:59,715 --> 00:30:02,707
...by a dodge as pathetically dimwitted
as an Aging Potion.

382
00:30:02,884 --> 00:30:07,127
-But that's why it's so brilliant.
-Because it's so pathetically dimwitted.

383
00:30:08,890 --> 00:30:10,881
-Ready, Fred?
-Ready, George.

384
00:30:11,059 --> 00:30:12,890
BOTH:
Bottoms up.

385
00:30:16,315 --> 00:30:18,226
-Yes!
-Yes!

386
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:20,557
Yeah!

387
00:30:21,737 --> 00:30:23,352
Yes!

388
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:25,270
Ready?

389
00:30:28,577 --> 00:30:30,738
FRED AND GEORGE:
Yes!

390
00:30:32,039 --> 00:30:34,280
[BOTH YELLING]

391
00:30:39,254 --> 00:30:41,245
-You said!
-You said!

392
00:30:42,215 --> 00:30:45,628
-Oh, right, you want a piece of me?!
-I'll tear your ears off!

393
00:30:45,802 --> 00:30:48,293
-Now you're making me laugh.
-Take this! Come on!

394
00:30:48,472 --> 00:30:49,928
[CHANTING]
<i>Fight! Fight! Fight!</i>

395
00:30:55,020 --> 00:30:56,760
FRED:
We're "old school," eh?

396
00:30:56,938 --> 00:30:59,304
GEORGE:
Yeah, but you look older!

397
00:31:17,918 --> 00:31:20,000
[BELL TOLLING]

398
00:31:22,923 --> 00:31:25,005
[CHATTERING]

399
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:33,342
DUMBLEDORE:
Sit down. Please.

400
00:31:36,770 --> 00:31:39,637
Now the moment
you've all been waiting for:

401
00:31:39,815 --> 00:31:41,931
The champion selection.

402
00:32:13,348 --> 00:32:17,182
The Durmstrang champion
is Viktor Krum.

403
00:32:17,394 --> 00:32:19,476
[CHEERING]

404
00:32:33,118 --> 00:32:35,530
The champion for Beauxbatons...

405
00:32:35,704 --> 00:32:37,695
...is Fleur Delacour.

406
00:32:37,914 --> 00:32:39,996
[CHEERING]

407
00:32:48,258 --> 00:32:51,250
The Hogwarts champion,
Cedric Diggory!

408
00:32:51,470 --> 00:32:53,552
[CHEERING]

409
00:33:01,313 --> 00:33:05,727
Excellent! We now have
our three champions.

410
00:33:05,901 --> 00:33:10,065
But in the end,
only one will go down in history.

411
00:33:10,238 --> 00:33:13,571
Only one will hoist
this chalice of champions...

412
00:33:13,909 --> 00:33:16,901
...this vessel of victory...

413
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:19,285
...the Triwizard Cup!

414
00:33:50,070 --> 00:33:51,731
Harry Potter.

415
00:33:53,823 --> 00:33:55,438
Harry Potter?

416
00:33:59,829 --> 00:34:02,036
No. No.

417
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:03,826
Harry Potter!

418
00:34:04,292 --> 00:34:05,782
Go on, Harry.

419
00:34:05,961 --> 00:34:07,701
Harry, for goodness sake.

420
00:34:35,782 --> 00:34:37,864
[WHISPERING]

421
00:34:39,202 --> 00:34:40,408
BOY 1:
He's a cheat!

422
00:34:40,954 --> 00:34:43,491
BOY 2:
He's not even 17 yet!

423
00:34:58,430 --> 00:35:00,512
[INSTRUMENTS WHIRRING
AND CLICKING]

424
00:35:11,359 --> 00:35:14,317
MAXIME: It's wrong, I tell you!
MOODY: You French tart.

425
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:16,318
Everything is a conspiracy theory!

426
00:35:16,489 --> 00:35:17,820
DUMBLEDORE:
Quiet! I can't think!

427
00:35:17,991 --> 00:35:20,198
-Everything is a conspiracy theory!
MAXIME: I protest.

428
00:35:20,368 --> 00:35:21,528
DUMBLEDORE: Harry.
-I protest!

429
00:35:21,703 --> 00:35:23,568
Did you put your name
in the Goblet of Fire?

430
00:35:23,747 --> 00:35:25,908
-No, sir.
-Did you ask one of the older students...

431
00:35:26,082 --> 00:35:27,413
-...to do it for you?
-No, sir.

432
00:35:27,584 --> 00:35:30,496
-You're absolutely sure?
-Yes. Yes, sir.

433
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:33,161
-But of course he is lying.
MOODY: The hell he is!

434
00:35:33,340 --> 00:35:35,752
The Goblet of Fire is an exceptionally
powerful magical object.

435
00:35:35,925 --> 00:35:39,042
Only an exceptionally powerful
Confundus Charm could've hoodwinked it.

436
00:35:39,220 --> 00:35:41,211
Magic way beyond the talents
of a fourth year.

437
00:35:41,389 --> 00:35:44,381
You seem to have given this
a fair bit of thought, Mad-Eye.

438
00:35:44,559 --> 00:35:47,722
It was once my job to think
as dark wizards do, Karkaroff...

439
00:35:47,896 --> 00:35:49,432
...perhaps you remember.

440
00:35:49,606 --> 00:35:52,018
DUMBLEDORE:
This doesn't help, Alastor.

441
00:35:52,734 --> 00:35:55,066
Leave this to you, Barty.

442
00:35:56,404 --> 00:35:58,611
The rules are absolute.

443
00:35:59,824 --> 00:36:03,567
The Goblet of Fire constitutes
a binding magical contract.

444
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:07,287
Mr. Potter has no choice.

445
00:36:08,083 --> 00:36:10,369
He is, as of tonight...

446
00:36:12,253 --> 00:36:14,244
...a Triwizard champion.

447
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,316
McGONAGALL:
This can't go on, Albus.

448
00:36:44,661 --> 00:36:47,494
First the Dark Mark. Now this?

449
00:36:47,664 --> 00:36:49,655
What do you suggest, Minerva?

450
00:36:50,834 --> 00:36:52,916
Put an end to it.

451
00:36:53,378 --> 00:36:55,369
Don't let Potter compete.

452
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:58,004
You heard Barty. The rules are clear.

453
00:36:58,174 --> 00:37:01,007
Well, the devil with Barty
and his rules.

454
00:37:01,177 --> 00:37:03,634
And since when did you
accommodate the Ministry?

455
00:37:03,805 --> 00:37:07,798
Headmaster, l, too, find it difficult
to believe this mere coincidence.

456
00:37:07,976 --> 00:37:11,889
However, if we are to truly discover
the meaning of these events...

457
00:37:12,063 --> 00:37:15,647
...perhaps we should,
for the time being...

458
00:37:16,568 --> 00:37:18,809
...Let them unfold.

459
00:37:18,987 --> 00:37:21,148
What--? Do nothing?

460
00:37:21,322 --> 00:37:22,983
Offer him up as bait?

461
00:37:23,992 --> 00:37:26,825
Potter is a boy, not a piece of meat.

462
00:37:27,704 --> 00:37:30,446
I agree. With Severus.

463
00:37:30,999 --> 00:37:35,038
-Alastor, keep an eye on Harry, will you?
-I can do that.

464
00:37:35,211 --> 00:37:39,955
Don't let him know, though.
He must be anxious enough as it is...

465
00:37:40,508 --> 00:37:43,170
...knowing what lies ahead.

466
00:37:43,511 --> 00:37:46,093
Then again, we all are.

467
00:37:47,223 --> 00:37:50,181
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

468
00:38:00,987 --> 00:38:02,773
How did you do it?

469
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:06,856
Never mind. Doesn't matter.

470
00:38:07,035 --> 00:38:08,946
Might've let
your best friend know, though.

471
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:12,362
-Let you know what?
-You know bloody well what.

472
00:38:12,540 --> 00:38:14,906
I didn't ask for this to happen, Ron.

473
00:38:15,376 --> 00:38:16,991
Okay?

474
00:38:17,170 --> 00:38:19,661
-You're being stupid.
-Yeah, that's me.

475
00:38:19,839 --> 00:38:23,377
Ron Weasley,
Harry Potter's stupid friend.

476
00:38:27,055 --> 00:38:29,046
I didn't put my name in that cup.

477
00:38:29,474 --> 00:38:33,308
I don't want eternal glory.
I just wanna be....

478
00:38:35,063 --> 00:38:37,520
Look, I don't know
what happened tonight...

479
00:38:37,690 --> 00:38:39,555
...and I don't know why.

480
00:38:39,734 --> 00:38:40,940
It just did.

481
00:38:41,820 --> 00:38:43,401
Okay?

482
00:38:52,205 --> 00:38:53,945
Piss off.

483
00:39:05,134 --> 00:39:06,965
[FLASH BULB CLICKS]

484
00:39:08,972 --> 00:39:11,429
What a charismatic quartet.

485
00:39:12,767 --> 00:39:14,382
Hello.

486
00:39:15,270 --> 00:39:17,807
I'm Rita Skeeter.

487
00:39:18,398 --> 00:39:20,889
I write for the Daily Prophet.

488
00:39:21,484 --> 00:39:26,194
But of course you know that, don't you?
It's you we don't know.

489
00:39:26,739 --> 00:39:28,570
You're the juicy news.

490
00:39:28,741 --> 00:39:32,950
What quirks lurk
beneath those rosy cheeks?

491
00:39:33,121 --> 00:39:36,613
What mysteries do the muscles mask?

492
00:39:36,791 --> 00:39:39,999
Does courage lie beneath those curls?

493
00:39:40,169 --> 00:39:43,206
In short, what makes a champion tick?

494
00:39:43,715 --> 00:39:48,004
"Me, Myself & l" want to know.
Not to mention my rabid readers.

495
00:39:48,177 --> 00:39:50,668
So who's feeling up to sharing?

496
00:39:50,889 --> 00:39:52,971
Hm?

497
00:39:53,975 --> 00:39:56,591
Shall we start with the youngest?
Lovely.

498
00:40:08,865 --> 00:40:10,651
This is cozy.

499
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:12,948
It's a broom cupboard.

500
00:40:13,328 --> 00:40:15,614
You should feel right at home, then.

501
00:40:15,830 --> 00:40:18,572
Don't mind if I use
a Quick-Quotes Quill, do you?

502
00:40:18,750 --> 00:40:20,331
Oh, no.

503
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:22,659
So tell me, Harry.

504
00:40:22,837 --> 00:40:25,749
Here you sit, a mere boy of 12--

505
00:40:25,924 --> 00:40:27,414
I'm 14. Sorry.

506
00:40:27,592 --> 00:40:30,550
--about to compete
against three students...

507
00:40:30,720 --> 00:40:34,008
...not only vastly more
emotionally mature than yourself...

508
00:40:34,182 --> 00:40:36,764
...but who have mastered spells
that you wouldn't attempt...

509
00:40:36,935 --> 00:40:39,267
...in your dizziest daydreams.

510
00:40:39,771 --> 00:40:41,807
Concerned?

511
00:40:42,565 --> 00:40:45,807
I-- I don't know.
I haven't really thought about it.

512
00:40:45,985 --> 00:40:47,850
RITA:
Just ignore the quill.

513
00:40:48,321 --> 00:40:50,858
Then, of course,
you're no ordinary boy of 12, are you?

514
00:40:51,032 --> 00:40:53,614
-Fourteen.
-Your story's legend.

515
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:56,530
Do you think it was
the trauma of your past...

516
00:40:56,704 --> 00:40:59,946
...that made you so keen to enter
such a dangerous tournament?

517
00:41:00,124 --> 00:41:01,864
No, I didn't enter.

518
00:41:02,043 --> 00:41:03,658
Of course you didn't.

519
00:41:05,922 --> 00:41:07,537
Everyone loves a rebel, Harry.

520
00:41:09,884 --> 00:41:11,340
Scratch that last.

521
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:14,840
Speaking of your parents,
were they alive...

522
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:16,379
...how do you think they'd feel?

523
00:41:16,557 --> 00:41:18,297
Proud? Or concerned...

524
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:22,310
...that your attitude shows, at best,
a pathological need for attention...

525
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:25,062
...at worst, a psychotic death wish?

526
00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:31,152
Hey, my eyes aren't
"glistening with the ghosts of my past."

527
00:41:32,615 --> 00:41:34,355
[SCREECHING]

528
00:42:03,438 --> 00:42:05,770
SIRIUS:
<i>Harry, I couldn't risk sending Hedwig.</i>

529
00:42:05,940 --> 00:42:09,228
<i>Since the World Cup, the Ministry's
been intercepting more and more owls...</i>

530
00:42:09,402 --> 00:42:11,609
<i>...and she's too easily recognized.</i>

531
00:42:11,779 --> 00:42:14,646
<i>We need to talk, Harry, face-to-face.</i>

532
00:42:14,824 --> 00:42:18,988
<i>Meet me in the Gryffindor common room,
1:00 this Saturday night,</i>

533
00:42:19,162 --> 00:42:20,948
<i>And make sure you're alone.</i>

534
00:42:21,122 --> 00:42:22,612
<i>Sirius.</i>

535
00:42:22,790 --> 00:42:24,280
-<i>P. S.:</i>
-Aah!

536
00:42:24,459 --> 00:42:26,245
<i>The bird bites.</i>

537
00:42:27,211 --> 00:42:28,246
Aah.

538
00:42:36,596 --> 00:42:38,006
Sirius?

539
00:42:54,906 --> 00:42:56,817
RITA:
<i>Harry Potter, age 12,..</i>

540
00:42:56,991 --> 00:42:59,949
<i>...suspect entrant
in the Triwizard Tournament.</i>

541
00:43:00,119 --> 00:43:02,701
<i>His eyes swimming
with the ghosts of his past...</i>

542
00:43:02,872 --> 00:43:04,453
<i>...and choking back tears...</i> Aah!

543
00:43:07,251 --> 00:43:08,832
[FIRE HISSES]

544
00:43:11,464 --> 00:43:13,125
[HISSES]

545
00:43:17,345 --> 00:43:19,757
[GASPS]

546
00:43:19,931 --> 00:43:22,513
Sirius. How--?

547
00:43:22,683 --> 00:43:25,174
I don't have much time,
so let me get straight to it.

548
00:43:25,353 --> 00:43:28,311
Did you or did you not put your name
into the Goblet of Fire?

549
00:43:28,481 --> 00:43:29,937
-No!
-Shh.

550
00:43:30,525 --> 00:43:31,810
I had to ask.

551
00:43:31,984 --> 00:43:36,774
Now, tell me about this dream of yours.
You mentioned Wormtail and Voldemort.

552
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:39,360
But who was the third man in the room?

553
00:43:39,534 --> 00:43:42,025
-I don't know.
-You didn't hear a name?

554
00:43:42,870 --> 00:43:44,406
No.

555
00:43:45,331 --> 00:43:49,040
Voldemort was giving him a job to do.
Something important.

556
00:43:49,210 --> 00:43:50,495
And what was that?

557
00:43:52,713 --> 00:43:54,328
He wanted...

558
00:43:54,507 --> 00:43:56,168
...me.

559
00:43:56,717 --> 00:44:01,051
I don't know why. But he was
gonna use this man to get to me.

560
00:44:02,348 --> 00:44:04,430
But, I mean, it was only a dream, right?

561
00:44:04,892 --> 00:44:06,507
Yes.

562
00:44:06,686 --> 00:44:08,222
It's just a dream.

563
00:44:08,980 --> 00:44:10,390
Look, Harry.

564
00:44:10,565 --> 00:44:14,057
The Death Eaters at the World Cup,
your name rising from that goblet...

565
00:44:14,235 --> 00:44:18,228
...these are not just coincidences.
Hogwarts isn't safe anymore.

566
00:44:18,406 --> 00:44:19,486
What are you saying?

567
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:23,900
I'm saying the devils are inside
the walls. Igor Karkaroff?

568
00:44:24,078 --> 00:44:28,447
He was a Death Eater. And no one,
no one stops being a Death Eater.

569
00:44:28,666 --> 00:44:31,032
Then there's Barty Crouch.
Heart of stone.

570
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:32,700
Sent his own son to Azkaban.

571
00:44:32,879 --> 00:44:34,835
[DOOR OPENING IN DISTANCE]

572
00:44:38,885 --> 00:44:40,967
You think one of them
put my name in the goblet?

573
00:44:41,137 --> 00:44:43,423
I haven't a clue who put your name
in that goblet...

574
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:47,591
...but whoever did is no friend to you.
People die in this tournament.

575
00:44:47,768 --> 00:44:51,181
-I'm not ready for this, Sirius.
-You don't have a choice.

576
00:44:51,355 --> 00:44:52,970
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

577
00:44:54,775 --> 00:44:57,187
-Someone's coming.
-Keep your friends close, Harry.

578
00:45:00,489 --> 00:45:02,445
-Who were you talking to?
-What?

579
00:45:02,617 --> 00:45:05,029
-Who says I was talking to anyone?
-I heard voices.

580
00:45:05,328 --> 00:45:09,321
Maybe you're imagining things.
Wouldn't be the first time.

581
00:45:09,874 --> 00:45:13,207
You're probably just practicing
for your next interview, I expect.

582
00:45:39,153 --> 00:45:40,768
NEVILLE:
Amazing.

583
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:46,028
-Amazing!
-Neville. You're doing it again.

584
00:45:46,202 --> 00:45:48,409
Oh, right, sorry.

585
00:45:49,288 --> 00:45:52,280
"Magical Water Plants
of the Highland Lochs"?

586
00:45:52,458 --> 00:45:55,621
Moody gave it to me.
That day we had tea.

587
00:45:57,129 --> 00:45:58,835
It's already been through enough people.

588
00:45:59,006 --> 00:46:01,122
Why don't you just go
and talk to him yourself?

589
00:46:02,593 --> 00:46:04,925
Ron, this is your problem, not mine.

590
00:46:05,096 --> 00:46:06,711
What do you want me to say again?

591
00:46:06,889 --> 00:46:08,675
You do it. Go.

592
00:46:11,644 --> 00:46:15,728
Ronald would like me to tell you
that Seamus told him...

593
00:46:16,357 --> 00:46:19,975
...that Dean was told by Parvati
that Hagrid's looking for you.

594
00:46:20,152 --> 00:46:22,564
Is that right? Well, you--

595
00:46:22,738 --> 00:46:23,818
What?

596
00:46:24,699 --> 00:46:26,314
Uh....

597
00:46:28,911 --> 00:46:31,869
-Are you sure you won't do this?
-You do it.

598
00:46:34,667 --> 00:46:37,625
Dean was told by Parvati that....

599
00:46:38,879 --> 00:46:41,086
Please don't ask me to say it again.

600
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:42,921
Hagrid's looking for you.

601
00:46:43,426 --> 00:46:46,509
-Well, you can tell Ronald--
-I'm not an owl!

602
00:46:56,981 --> 00:46:59,393
HAGRID: Did you bring
your father's cloak, like I asked you?

603
00:46:59,567 --> 00:47:02,058
HARRY: Yeah, I brought the cloak.
Hagrid, where are we going?

604
00:47:02,236 --> 00:47:03,646
You'll see soon enough.

605
00:47:03,821 --> 00:47:06,028
Now pay attention, this is important.

606
00:47:07,742 --> 00:47:09,152
What's with the flower?

607
00:47:10,244 --> 00:47:12,656
Hagrid, have you combed your hair?

608
00:47:13,080 --> 00:47:14,786
As a matter of fact, I have.

609
00:47:15,249 --> 00:47:18,161
You might like to try the same thing
now and again.

610
00:47:18,586 --> 00:47:21,328
[DISTANT ROARING]

611
00:47:22,548 --> 00:47:24,630
[SNARLING]

612
00:47:26,677 --> 00:47:28,133
MAXIME:
Hagrid?

613
00:47:32,058 --> 00:47:33,889
The cloak! Put the cloak on!

614
00:47:40,483 --> 00:47:43,896
-Bonsoir, Olympe.
-Oh, Hagrid.

615
00:47:44,070 --> 00:47:47,779
I thought perhaps you weren't coming.
I thought perhaps...

616
00:47:47,948 --> 00:47:50,610
...you had forgotten me.

617
00:47:50,785 --> 00:47:52,741
Couldn't forget you, Olympe.

618
00:47:53,412 --> 00:47:55,152
-Ugh.
-What is it you wanted to show me?

619
00:47:56,916 --> 00:48:00,124
When we spoke earlier,
you sounded so...

620
00:48:00,461 --> 00:48:01,951
...exhilarated.

621
00:48:02,546 --> 00:48:05,379
You'll be glad you came. Trust me.

622
00:48:06,717 --> 00:48:08,457
[ROARING]

623
00:48:08,636 --> 00:48:10,627
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

624
00:48:15,976 --> 00:48:17,716
MAXIME:
Can we get closer?

625
00:48:25,528 --> 00:48:26,984
Dragons?

626
00:48:27,154 --> 00:48:28,644
That's the first task?

627
00:48:29,073 --> 00:48:31,029
-You're joking.
HAGRID: Come on, Harry.

628
00:48:32,368 --> 00:48:35,405
These are seriously
misunderstood creatures.

629
00:48:36,497 --> 00:48:37,987
Oh, crikey!

630
00:48:38,541 --> 00:48:40,623
Although, I have to admit...

631
00:48:40,793 --> 00:48:43,626
...that Horntail is a right nasty
piece of work.

632
00:48:43,796 --> 00:48:46,538
Poor Ron nearly fainted
just seeing him, you know.

633
00:48:48,134 --> 00:48:50,170
-Ron was here?
-Oh, sure.

634
00:48:50,344 --> 00:48:53,836
His brother Charlie helped
to bring him over from Romania.

635
00:48:54,014 --> 00:48:55,379
Didn't Ron tell you that?

636
00:48:57,393 --> 00:48:58,803
No, he didn't.

637
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:01,385
He didn't tell me a thing.

638
00:49:11,365 --> 00:49:14,448
BOY 1: You cheat, Potter.
BOY 2: You stink, Potter.

639
00:49:15,953 --> 00:49:18,615
-Good luck, Potter.
BOY 3: Potter stinks!

640
00:49:18,789 --> 00:49:21,451
-Cedric rules.
HARRY: Thanks.

641
00:49:22,543 --> 00:49:24,204
Like the badge?

642
00:49:24,753 --> 00:49:26,493
Excuse me.

643
00:49:30,676 --> 00:49:32,132
BOY 1:
Harry.

644
00:49:32,720 --> 00:49:34,676
Hey! Read the badge, Potter!

645
00:49:34,847 --> 00:49:36,337
Can I have a word?

646
00:49:37,308 --> 00:49:39,173
-All right.
BOY 2: You stink, Potter!

647
00:49:39,351 --> 00:49:42,343
BOY 3: Potter, you stink!
BOY 4: Harry Potter smells!

648
00:49:44,857 --> 00:49:47,394
Dragons. That's the first task.

649
00:49:47,568 --> 00:49:50,731
-They've got one for each of us.
BOY 2: Come on, Ced!

650
00:49:50,905 --> 00:49:52,896
Are you serious?

651
00:49:53,699 --> 00:49:56,736
And Fleur and Krum, do they--?

652
00:49:56,911 --> 00:49:59,027
-Yes.
BOY 2: Come on, Ced, leave him.

653
00:49:59,205 --> 00:50:00,786
CEDRIC: Right.
BOY 2: He's not worth it.

654
00:50:00,956 --> 00:50:03,538
BOY 1: Read the badges, Potter!
-Hey, listen. About the badges.

655
00:50:03,709 --> 00:50:06,667
-I've asked them not to wear them, but--
-Don't worry about it.

656
00:50:06,837 --> 00:50:09,249
It's not like I try
to blow things up, exactly.

657
00:50:09,965 --> 00:50:11,421
It just happens a fair bit.

658
00:50:11,592 --> 00:50:14,675
You have to admit, though,
fire's pretty fascinating.

659
00:50:14,845 --> 00:50:16,710
You're a right foul git, you know that?

660
00:50:16,889 --> 00:50:19,096
-You think so?
-I know so.

661
00:50:19,266 --> 00:50:20,597
Anything else?

662
00:50:20,768 --> 00:50:24,260
-Yeah. Stay away from me.
-Fine.

663
00:50:26,649 --> 00:50:30,267
CRABBE: There's Potter. Cheat.
MALFOY: Why so tense, Potter?

664
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:33,440
My father and I have a bet, you see.

665
00:50:33,614 --> 00:50:36,777
I don't think you're gonna last
10 minutes in this tournament.

666
00:50:39,370 --> 00:50:42,282
He disagrees.
He thinks you won't last five.

667
00:50:42,456 --> 00:50:45,573
I don't give a damn
what your father thinks, Malfoy.

668
00:50:46,585 --> 00:50:50,578
He's vile and cruel.
And you're just pathetic.

669
00:50:51,507 --> 00:50:53,998
-Pathetic?
-Oh, no, you don't, sonny!

670
00:50:54,218 --> 00:50:55,628
Aah!

671
00:50:56,262 --> 00:50:59,129
MOODY: I'll teach you to curse someone
when their back is turned!

672
00:50:59,306 --> 00:51:03,140
You stinking, cowardly, scummy...

673
00:51:03,310 --> 00:51:05,050
-Professor Moody!
-...back-shooting--

674
00:51:05,229 --> 00:51:08,141
-What are you doing?
-Teaching.

675
00:51:09,149 --> 00:51:12,687
-Is that a--? Is that a student?
-Technically, it's a ferret.

676
00:51:12,861 --> 00:51:15,147
Oh! Ah!

677
00:51:18,993 --> 00:51:20,858
Stand still! Stand still!

678
00:51:31,839 --> 00:51:34,046
-My father will hear about this!
-Is that a threat?

679
00:51:34,216 --> 00:51:36,172
-Professor Moody!
-Is that a threat?

680
00:51:36,343 --> 00:51:38,208
Professor!

681
00:51:38,387 --> 00:51:41,925
I could tell you stories about your father
that would curl even your greasy hair!

682
00:51:42,099 --> 00:51:44,806
-Alastor! Alastor.
-It doesn't end here!

683
00:51:44,977 --> 00:51:48,765
We never use transfiguration
as a punishment!

684
00:51:48,939 --> 00:51:51,146
Surely Dumbledore told you that.

685
00:51:51,692 --> 00:51:56,152
-He might've mentioned it.
-Well, you will do well to remember it.

686
00:51:57,239 --> 00:51:58,695
Away!

687
00:52:01,827 --> 00:52:04,034
You. Come with me.

688
00:52:09,084 --> 00:52:10,995
[GRUNTS]

689
00:52:12,630 --> 00:52:14,086
[GROANS]

690
00:52:39,239 --> 00:52:41,321
That's a Foe-Glass.

691
00:52:42,076 --> 00:52:44,158
Lets me keep an eye on my enemies.

692
00:52:44,620 --> 00:52:49,034
If I can see the whites of their eyes,
they're standing right behind me.

693
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:52,366
[RUMBLING]
[DISTANT SHOUTING]

694
00:52:53,212 --> 00:52:55,669
Wouldn't even bother telling you
what's in there.

695
00:52:55,839 --> 00:52:57,875
You wouldn't believe it if I did.

696
00:52:58,133 --> 00:52:59,839
Now...

697
00:53:01,512 --> 00:53:04,345
...what are you going to do
about your dragon?

698
00:53:04,515 --> 00:53:07,052
Oh, um....

699
00:53:08,268 --> 00:53:10,554
Well, you know, I just thought I'd....

700
00:53:12,022 --> 00:53:13,512
Sit.

701
00:53:17,236 --> 00:53:18,601
Listen to me, Potter.

702
00:53:19,613 --> 00:53:20,773
Your pal Diggory?

703
00:53:20,948 --> 00:53:25,362
By your age, he could turn a whistle into
a watch and have it sing you the time.

704
00:53:26,578 --> 00:53:27,818
Miss Delacour?

705
00:53:28,247 --> 00:53:30,954
She's as much a fairy princess as I am.

706
00:53:31,458 --> 00:53:35,042
As for Krum, his head
may be filled with sawdust...

707
00:53:35,212 --> 00:53:37,373
...but Karkaroff's is not.

708
00:53:37,548 --> 00:53:39,379
They'll have a strategy.

709
00:53:39,550 --> 00:53:43,008
And you can bet that it will
play to Krum's strengths.

710
00:53:47,850 --> 00:53:49,431
Come on, Potter.

711
00:53:49,601 --> 00:53:51,683
What are your strengths?

712
00:53:51,854 --> 00:53:53,094
Um....

713
00:53:53,272 --> 00:53:54,637
I don't know.

714
00:53:54,815 --> 00:53:57,602
Well, I can fly.
I mean, I'm a fair flyer. But l....

715
00:53:57,776 --> 00:54:01,815
-Better than fair, the way I heard it.
-But I'm not allowed a broom.

716
00:54:01,989 --> 00:54:05,607
You're allowed a wand.

717
00:54:12,040 --> 00:54:13,496
FRED:
Bets! Place your bets!

718
00:54:13,667 --> 00:54:15,828
GEORGE:
Bets taken! Bets taken here!

719
00:54:16,003 --> 00:54:18,961
Step up, folks! Who fancies a flutter
in today's bloodbath?

720
00:54:19,131 --> 00:54:21,918
Smart money's on Krum to survive!
Any bets?

721
00:54:22,176 --> 00:54:23,666
Yes, sir?

722
00:54:24,011 --> 00:54:26,673
Ten-to-1 for Fleur. There you go.
Thank you very much.

723
00:54:27,222 --> 00:54:29,178
DUMBLEDORE:
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

724
00:54:29,391 --> 00:54:32,007
<i>This is a great day for all of us.</i>

725
00:54:32,186 --> 00:54:34,222
[DRAGON ROARING]

726
00:54:35,439 --> 00:54:39,682
<i>Each of the three tasks involves
very considerable danger.</i>

727
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:42,522
<i>-Please keep your seats at all times.</i>
VOICE: Psst.

728
00:54:42,696 --> 00:54:45,438
<i>This will minimize any risks
you may be exposed to.</i>

729
00:54:45,616 --> 00:54:49,029
-Harry? Is that you?
-Yeah.

730
00:54:49,203 --> 00:54:50,909
<i>I'm sure we all wish our champions...</i>

731
00:54:51,079 --> 00:54:54,162
-How are you feeling? Okay?
-<i>...the greatest of luck.</i>

732
00:54:56,460 --> 00:54:59,873
The key is to concentrate.
After that, you just have to--

733
00:55:00,047 --> 00:55:01,878
Battle a dragon.

734
00:55:02,174 --> 00:55:04,290
[WHIMPERS]

735
00:55:06,178 --> 00:55:08,635
RITA:
Young love.

736
00:55:08,847 --> 00:55:10,633
Oh, how...

737
00:55:13,101 --> 00:55:14,386
...stirring.

738
00:55:17,064 --> 00:55:20,227
If everything goes unfortunately today...

739
00:55:20,400 --> 00:55:23,187
...you two may even
make the front page.

740
00:55:23,362 --> 00:55:25,569
You have no business here.

741
00:55:25,739 --> 00:55:27,730
This tent is for champions...

742
00:55:28,116 --> 00:55:29,822
...and friends.

743
00:55:32,621 --> 00:55:36,785
No matter. We've got what we wanted.

744
00:55:39,920 --> 00:55:42,753
Good day, champions.
Gather round, please.

745
00:55:42,923 --> 00:55:47,087
Now, you've waited, you've wondered,
and at last the moment has arrived.

746
00:55:47,261 --> 00:55:50,503
A moment only four of you
can fully appreciate.

747
00:55:50,681 --> 00:55:52,672
What are you doing here, Miss Granger?

748
00:55:52,850 --> 00:55:55,762
Oh, um, sorry, I'll just go.

749
00:55:55,936 --> 00:55:57,472
Barty, the bag.

750
00:55:57,938 --> 00:56:00,145
Champions, in a circle around me.

751
00:56:00,315 --> 00:56:03,432
Miss Delacour, over here. Mr. Krum.

752
00:56:03,610 --> 00:56:07,523
And, Potter, Mr. Potter, over here.
That's right. Now...

753
00:56:07,698 --> 00:56:10,110
...Miss Delacour, if you will.

754
00:56:12,160 --> 00:56:13,525
[SNARLING]

755
00:56:14,204 --> 00:56:15,865
CROUCH:
The Welsh Green.

756
00:56:16,707 --> 00:56:18,789
[GROWLS]

757
00:56:20,502 --> 00:56:21,787
Mr. Krum.

758
00:56:24,798 --> 00:56:28,086
The Chinese Fireball. Ooh.

759
00:56:33,181 --> 00:56:35,593
The Swedish Short-Snout.

760
00:56:36,059 --> 00:56:38,050
-Which leaves....
-The Horntail.

761
00:56:38,228 --> 00:56:40,469
-What's that, boy?
-Nothing.

762
00:56:40,981 --> 00:56:42,346
[GRUNTS]

763
00:56:43,901 --> 00:56:46,313
CROUCH:
The Hungarian Horntail.

764
00:56:46,486 --> 00:56:48,317
[ROARING]

765
00:56:48,488 --> 00:56:51,605
These represent four
very real dragons...

766
00:56:51,783 --> 00:56:54,820
...each of which has been given
a golden egg to protect.

767
00:56:54,995 --> 00:56:57,486
Your objective is simple:

768
00:56:57,664 --> 00:56:59,154
Collect the egg.

769
00:56:59,333 --> 00:57:02,325
This you must do,
for each egg contains a clue...

770
00:57:02,502 --> 00:57:05,994
...without which you cannot hope
to proceed to the next task.

771
00:57:06,173 --> 00:57:07,504
Any questions?

772
00:57:08,508 --> 00:57:11,170
Very well. Good luck, champions.

773
00:57:11,345 --> 00:57:14,132
Mr. Diggory, at the sound of the cannon,
you may--

774
00:57:14,348 --> 00:57:16,509
[RITA SHRIEKING]

775
00:57:16,683 --> 00:57:18,924
[CROWD CHEERING]

776
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:26,648
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Diggory! Diggory! Diggory!</i>

777
00:57:38,205 --> 00:57:41,572
DUMBLEDORE: <i>Three of our champions
have now faced their dragons...</i>

778
00:57:41,750 --> 00:57:45,242
<i>...and so each one of them
will proceed to the next task,</i>

779
00:57:45,420 --> 00:57:48,912
<i>And now our fourth
and final contestant.</i>

780
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:54,468
CROWD [CHANTING]:
<i>Harry! Harry! Harry!</i>

781
00:58:19,663 --> 00:58:21,119
CROWD:
Oh!

782
00:58:21,331 --> 00:58:23,162
[DRAGON ROARING]
[CROWD SCREAMING]

783
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:25,331
[SCREECHES]

784
00:58:29,965 --> 00:58:32,081
[PANTS AND GRUNTS]

785
00:58:38,598 --> 00:58:40,463
[GASPING]

786
00:58:43,895 --> 00:58:45,101
Aah!

787
00:58:47,357 --> 00:58:48,642
[ROARS]

788
00:59:01,580 --> 00:59:04,492
Your wand, Harry! Your wand!

789
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:07,036
<i>Accio Firebolt!</i>

790
00:59:13,508 --> 00:59:15,214
[SCREECHES]

791
00:59:36,031 --> 00:59:38,192
-Yeah! Woo-hoo!
-Yes!

792
00:59:41,369 --> 00:59:42,700
Ooh.

793
00:59:47,125 --> 00:59:48,535
Oh, my God.

794
00:59:54,382 --> 00:59:56,919
[SCREAMING]

795
00:59:58,178 --> 01:00:01,466
-Yeah! Whoo!
-Yeah! Well done, dragon!

796
01:00:33,421 --> 01:00:36,254
[YELLING]

797
01:00:38,385 --> 01:00:40,341
[PANTING]

798
01:00:44,808 --> 01:00:46,969
[ROARS]

799
01:00:54,025 --> 01:00:56,107
[GROWLING]

800
01:00:59,072 --> 01:01:00,733
Aah!

801
01:01:05,036 --> 01:01:07,118
[GRUNTING]

802
01:01:10,292 --> 01:01:12,374
[ROARING]

803
01:01:30,312 --> 01:01:32,428
[YELLING]

804
01:02:01,801 --> 01:02:04,258
[YELLING]

805
01:02:08,600 --> 01:02:10,682
[SCREECHING]

806
01:02:15,899 --> 01:02:17,981
[CROWD MURMURING]

807
01:02:33,500 --> 01:02:35,661
Yes! Yes!

808
01:02:38,964 --> 01:02:40,670
[BROOM SPUTTERING]

809
01:02:58,858 --> 01:03:01,565
-Yes, Harry!
-Knew you wouldn't die. Lose a leg.

810
01:03:01,736 --> 01:03:03,692
-Or an arm.
-Pack it in altogether?

811
01:03:03,863 --> 01:03:05,603
BOTH:
Never!

812
01:03:07,701 --> 01:03:09,032
SEAMUS:
Shush!

813
01:03:09,536 --> 01:03:12,198
Go on, Harry. What's the clue?

814
01:03:13,206 --> 01:03:16,039
-Who wants me to open it?
ALL: Yes!

815
01:03:16,876 --> 01:03:19,367
-Do you want me to open it?
-Yes!

816
01:03:22,090 --> 01:03:23,671
[SCREECHING]

817
01:03:23,842 --> 01:03:25,673
[CROWD GROANING]

818
01:03:30,557 --> 01:03:32,969
What the bloody hell was that?

819
01:03:37,105 --> 01:03:39,847
All right, everyone!
Go back to your knitting.

820
01:03:40,025 --> 01:03:44,064
This is gonna be uncomfortable enough
without all you nosy sods listening in.

821
01:03:47,240 --> 01:03:51,153
I reckon you have to be barking mad to
put your own name in the Goblet of Fire.

822
01:03:51,578 --> 01:03:54,285
Caught on, have you?
Took you long enough.

823
01:03:55,415 --> 01:03:57,531
I wasn't the only one
who thought you'd done it.

824
01:03:57,709 --> 01:03:59,950
Everyone was saying it
behind your back.

825
01:04:02,172 --> 01:04:05,414
Brilliant.
That makes me feel loads better.

826
01:04:06,343 --> 01:04:09,710
-Least I warned you about the dragons.
-Hagrid warned me about the dragons.

827
01:04:09,888 --> 01:04:11,378
No, no, no, I did.

828
01:04:11,556 --> 01:04:14,593
No, don't you remember?
I told Hermione to tell you...

829
01:04:14,768 --> 01:04:18,807
...that Seamus told me that Parvati
told Dean that Hagrid was looking for you.

830
01:04:18,980 --> 01:04:22,939
Seamus never actually told me anything,
so it was really me all along.

831
01:04:23,943 --> 01:04:26,935
I thought we'd be all right, you know...

832
01:04:27,155 --> 01:04:29,146
...after you'd figured that out.

833
01:04:29,532 --> 01:04:32,194
Who--? Who could possibly
figure that out?

834
01:04:32,869 --> 01:04:34,279
That's completely mental.

835
01:04:34,454 --> 01:04:37,491
Yeah. Isn't it?

836
01:04:37,665 --> 01:04:39,701
I suppose I was a bit distraught.

837
01:04:42,295 --> 01:04:44,001
Boys.

838
01:04:47,175 --> 01:04:50,133
[OWLS SCREECHING]

839
01:05:05,568 --> 01:05:07,650
[WHISPERING]

840
01:05:08,488 --> 01:05:09,898
BOTH:
Hi, Harry.

841
01:05:13,535 --> 01:05:16,151
Cho, Harry's looking at you.

842
01:05:20,083 --> 01:05:21,789
CHO:
Shush.

843
01:05:22,502 --> 01:05:23,833
HERMIONE:
Look at this!

844
01:05:25,839 --> 01:05:28,330
I can't believe it! She's done it again.

845
01:05:29,384 --> 01:05:31,625
"Miss Granger,
a plain but ambitious girl...

846
01:05:31,803 --> 01:05:34,545
...seems to be developing a taste
for famous wizards.

847
01:05:34,722 --> 01:05:37,008
Her latest prey, sources report...

848
01:05:37,183 --> 01:05:40,801
...is none other than the
Bulgarian bonbon, Viktor Krum.

849
01:05:41,104 --> 01:05:45,017
No word yet on how Harry Potter's
taking this latest emotional blow."

850
01:05:46,401 --> 01:05:47,732
Parcel for you, Mr. Weasley.

851
01:05:47,902 --> 01:05:50,018
Oh, thank you, Nigel.

852
01:05:51,906 --> 01:05:53,897
[CLEARS THROAT]

853
01:05:54,826 --> 01:05:57,659
Not now, Nigel. Later.

854
01:05:59,497 --> 01:06:01,033
Go on.

855
01:06:06,379 --> 01:06:09,121
I told him I'd get him Harry's autograph.

856
01:06:11,342 --> 01:06:13,082
Oh, look, Mum's sent me something.

857
01:06:21,227 --> 01:06:23,058
Mum sent me a dress.

858
01:06:23,229 --> 01:06:27,063
Well, it does match your eyes.
Is there a bonnet? Aha.

859
01:06:27,525 --> 01:06:29,356
Nose down, Harry.

860
01:06:29,903 --> 01:06:33,771
-Ginny, these must be for you.
-I'm not wearing that, it's ghastly.

861
01:06:35,575 --> 01:06:37,406
What are you on about?

862
01:06:37,577 --> 01:06:39,533
They're not for Ginny.

863
01:06:39,704 --> 01:06:41,035
They're for you.

864
01:06:42,081 --> 01:06:45,824
-Dress robes.
-Dress robes? For what?

865
01:06:47,086 --> 01:06:50,544
McGONAGALL:
The Yule Ball has been a tradition...

866
01:06:50,715 --> 01:06:52,000
[RECORD SCRATCHING]

867
01:06:52,175 --> 01:06:54,757
...of the Triwizard Tournament...

868
01:06:55,470 --> 01:06:57,552
...since its inception.

869
01:06:58,223 --> 01:07:02,091
On Christmas Eve night,
we and our guests...

870
01:07:02,268 --> 01:07:03,929
...gather in the Great Hall...

871
01:07:04,103 --> 01:07:08,142
...for a night of well-mannered frivolity.

872
01:07:09,692 --> 01:07:11,933
As representatives of the host school...

873
01:07:12,111 --> 01:07:17,151
...I expect each and every one of you
to put your best foot forward.

874
01:07:17,534 --> 01:07:20,150
And I mean this literally, because...

875
01:07:20,328 --> 01:07:24,788
...the Yule Ball is, first and foremost...

876
01:07:25,625 --> 01:07:27,115
...a dance.

877
01:07:27,335 --> 01:07:29,246
[EXCITED CHATTERING]

878
01:07:29,462 --> 01:07:30,918
[GROANING]

879
01:07:31,381 --> 01:07:33,167
Silence!

880
01:07:33,383 --> 01:07:36,375
The house of Godric Gryffindor
has commanded the respect...

881
01:07:36,553 --> 01:07:39,169
...of the wizard world
for nearly 10 centuries.

882
01:07:39,347 --> 01:07:43,431
I will not have you, in the course of a
single evening, besmirching that name...

883
01:07:43,601 --> 01:07:47,810
...by behaving like a babbling,
bumbling band of baboons.

884
01:07:48,523 --> 01:07:50,479
Try saying that five times fast, huh?

885
01:07:50,650 --> 01:07:52,140
McGONAGALL:
Now, to dance...

886
01:07:52,318 --> 01:07:56,027
...is to let the body breathe.

887
01:07:56,197 --> 01:07:59,530
Inside every girl,
a secret swan slumbers...

888
01:07:59,701 --> 01:08:02,067
...longing to burst forth
and take flight.

889
01:08:02,245 --> 01:08:06,238
Something's about to burst out of Eloise
Midgen, but I don't think it's a swan.

890
01:08:06,416 --> 01:08:09,533
Inside every boy,
a lordly lion prepared to prance.

891
01:08:09,711 --> 01:08:11,952
-Mr. Weasley.
-Yes?

892
01:08:12,130 --> 01:08:14,542
Will you join me, please?

893
01:08:19,178 --> 01:08:22,670
Now, place your right hand
on my waist.

894
01:08:22,849 --> 01:08:24,760
-Where?
-My waist.

895
01:08:24,934 --> 01:08:25,969
[BOY WHISTLES]

896
01:08:26,144 --> 01:08:28,135
And extend your arm.

897
01:08:28,605 --> 01:08:30,561
Mr. Filch, if you please.

898
01:08:32,358 --> 01:08:33,814
[BALLROOM MUSIC PLAYING]

899
01:08:33,985 --> 01:08:35,646
One, two, three.

900
01:08:35,820 --> 01:08:39,312
One, two, three. One, two, three.

901
01:08:39,490 --> 01:08:41,105
[HUMMING]

902
01:08:41,284 --> 01:08:42,740
HARRY:
Oi!

903
01:08:43,036 --> 01:08:45,152
Never gonna let him forget this,
are you?

904
01:08:45,330 --> 01:08:46,490
BOTH:
Never.

905
01:08:46,664 --> 01:08:48,074
McGONAGALL:
Everybody come together.

906
01:08:48,249 --> 01:08:50,535
Boys, on your feet!

907
01:09:02,639 --> 01:09:04,755
[HUMMING]

908
01:09:13,608 --> 01:09:15,564
Why do they have to travel in packs?

909
01:09:15,735 --> 01:09:18,351
How are you supposed to get one
on their own to ask them?

910
01:09:26,245 --> 01:09:29,737
Blimey, Harry. You've slayed dragons.
If you can't get a date, who can?

911
01:09:29,916 --> 01:09:32,157
I think I'd take the dragon right now.

912
01:09:38,383 --> 01:09:39,919
I take after my mum.

913
01:09:40,093 --> 01:09:44,052
Though I didn't know her very well.
She left when I was about 3.

914
01:09:44,222 --> 01:09:46,133
No, not the maternal sort, her.

915
01:09:46,307 --> 01:09:49,891
Broke me dad's heart, though.
He was a tiny little fella, my dad.

916
01:09:50,061 --> 01:09:54,600
I could pick him up at the age of 6 with
one hand and put him up on the dresser.

917
01:09:54,774 --> 01:09:57,106
He laughed so hard at that.

918
01:09:59,153 --> 01:10:01,018
Very funny.

919
01:10:06,953 --> 01:10:10,696
And then he died
just when I started school, so....

920
01:10:10,873 --> 01:10:13,910
So I sort of had to make
me own way, as it were.

921
01:10:14,335 --> 01:10:16,496
But enough of me. What about you?

922
01:10:20,049 --> 01:10:22,005
[GIRLS CHATTERING AND GIGGLING]

923
01:10:25,930 --> 01:10:28,012
[HERMIONE CLEARS THROAT]

924
01:10:33,771 --> 01:10:38,856
This is mad. At this rate, we'll be
the only ones in our year without dates.

925
01:10:41,154 --> 01:10:43,861
Well, us and Neville.

926
01:10:44,031 --> 01:10:46,693
Yeah, but, then again,
he can take himself.

927
01:10:47,452 --> 01:10:50,194
It might interest you to know
that Neville's already got someone.

928
01:10:50,371 --> 01:10:51,656
[GROANS]

929
01:10:53,249 --> 01:10:54,989
Now I'm really depressed.

930
01:11:00,840 --> 01:11:04,253
[WHISPERS] "Get a move on or all
the good ones will have gone."

931
01:11:06,345 --> 01:11:08,336
Who you going with, then?

932
01:11:11,058 --> 01:11:12,764
FRED: Oi, Angelina?
[MOUTHS] What?

933
01:11:12,935 --> 01:11:18,225
[WHISPERS]
Do you wanna go to the ball with me?

934
01:11:18,566 --> 01:11:20,306
To the ball?

935
01:11:20,485 --> 01:11:21,895
Yeah, all right.

936
01:11:25,656 --> 01:11:27,192
Oi, Hermione.

937
01:11:27,366 --> 01:11:29,027
You're a girl.

938
01:11:29,202 --> 01:11:30,533
Very well spotted.

939
01:11:30,703 --> 01:11:32,614
Come with one of us?

940
01:11:32,955 --> 01:11:34,240
[GRUNTS]

941
01:11:37,251 --> 01:11:40,163
Come on. It's one thing for a bloke
to show up alone.

942
01:11:40,338 --> 01:11:41,828
For a girl, it's just sad.

943
01:11:42,006 --> 01:11:45,749
I won't be going alone, because,
believe it or not, someone's asked me!

944
01:11:52,725 --> 01:11:54,716
And I said yes!

945
01:11:56,562 --> 01:11:58,143
Bloody hell.

946
01:11:58,314 --> 01:11:59,975
She's lying, right?

947
01:12:00,149 --> 01:12:01,355
If you say so.

948
01:12:02,068 --> 01:12:05,401
RON: Look, we've just gotta
grit our teeth and do it.

949
01:12:05,571 --> 01:12:07,653
Tonight, when we get back
to the common room...

950
01:12:07,824 --> 01:12:09,530
...we'll both have partners. Agreed?

951
01:12:09,700 --> 01:12:11,190
Agreed.

952
01:12:11,369 --> 01:12:12,779
[BOTH GRUNT]

953
01:12:25,424 --> 01:12:27,289
[OWL SCREECHES]

954
01:12:33,850 --> 01:12:35,386
[GASPS]

955
01:12:35,560 --> 01:12:36,640
-Cho!
-Harry!

956
01:12:36,811 --> 01:12:38,893
[LAUGHING NERVOUSLY]

957
01:12:39,897 --> 01:12:43,185
Um, watch yourself on the stairs.
It's a bit icy at the top.

958
01:12:43,359 --> 01:12:44,940
Okay, thanks.

959
01:12:49,407 --> 01:12:50,442
Cho?

960
01:12:51,409 --> 01:12:52,945
-Yes?
-Um....

961
01:12:54,328 --> 01:12:55,784
Well, I just wondered if you--

962
01:12:55,955 --> 01:12:56,990
[OWLS SQUAWKING]

963
01:12:57,164 --> 01:12:59,496
I wondered if maybe
you wanted to go to the ball with me.

964
01:13:01,210 --> 01:13:03,451
Sorry, I didn't catch that.

965
01:13:04,380 --> 01:13:09,295
I was just wondering if maybe
you wanted to go to the ball with me.

966
01:13:11,345 --> 01:13:13,336
Oh, um....

967
01:13:15,308 --> 01:13:16,889
Harry...

968
01:13:17,059 --> 01:13:19,892
...I'm sorry, but someone's
already asked me.

969
01:13:20,897 --> 01:13:22,307
And....

970
01:13:22,982 --> 01:13:26,224
Well, I've said I'll go with him.

971
01:13:27,904 --> 01:13:30,395
Okay. Yeah. Great.

972
01:13:31,782 --> 01:13:34,489
Fine. No problem.

973
01:13:34,827 --> 01:13:36,408
Okay. Good.

974
01:13:37,872 --> 01:13:39,408
Harry?

975
01:13:40,041 --> 01:13:41,827
I really am...

976
01:13:42,001 --> 01:13:43,662
...sorry.

977
01:13:52,136 --> 01:13:53,251
[SIGHS]

978
01:13:53,429 --> 01:13:54,919
It's all right, Ron.

979
01:13:55,097 --> 01:13:58,305
It's okay, Ron. It's all right.
It doesn't matter.

980
01:13:58,476 --> 01:14:00,341
HARRY:
What happened to you?

981
01:14:00,603 --> 01:14:02,764
He just asked Fleur Delacour out.

982
01:14:02,939 --> 01:14:05,430
-What?
-What did she say?

983
01:14:05,608 --> 01:14:06,973
No, of course.

984
01:14:08,527 --> 01:14:11,860
-She said yes?
RON: Don't be silly.

985
01:14:12,281 --> 01:14:16,695
There she was, walking by.
You know how I like it when they walk.

986
01:14:17,453 --> 01:14:21,071
I couldn't help it.
It just sort of slipped out.

987
01:14:21,248 --> 01:14:24,661
Actually, he sort of screamed at her.
It was a bit frightening.

988
01:14:25,878 --> 01:14:29,496
-And what did you do then?
-What else? I ran for it.

989
01:14:29,674 --> 01:14:33,383
I'm not cut out for this, Harry.
I don't know what got into me.

990
01:14:33,552 --> 01:14:34,792
BOTH:
Hi, Harry.

991
01:14:34,971 --> 01:14:38,054
RON: I always liked looking at them
from behind.

992
01:14:39,392 --> 01:14:41,929
She's never gonna forgive me, ever.

993
01:14:42,520 --> 01:14:43,555
Hey!

994
01:14:44,105 --> 01:14:47,142
[BALLROOM MUSIC PLAYS]

995
01:14:48,859 --> 01:14:50,941
[CHATTERING]

996
01:15:00,663 --> 01:15:02,369
RON:
Bloody hell.

997
01:15:04,583 --> 01:15:06,369
Bloody hell.

998
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:11,165
Bloody....

999
01:15:11,340 --> 01:15:12,546
Oh, bloody....

1000
01:15:16,262 --> 01:15:18,969
What are those? What are those?

1001
01:15:19,140 --> 01:15:22,177
-My dress robes.
-Well, they're all right!

1002
01:15:22,351 --> 01:15:25,263
No lace. No dodgy little collar.

1003
01:15:25,438 --> 01:15:27,429
Well, I expect yours are more traditional.

1004
01:15:27,606 --> 01:15:32,521
Traditional?! They're ancient!
I look like my Great Aunt Tessie!

1005
01:15:33,738 --> 01:15:34,773
[SNIFFS]

1006
01:15:34,947 --> 01:15:38,030
I smell like my Great Aunt Tessie.

1007
01:15:42,788 --> 01:15:44,619
Murder me, Harry.

1008
01:15:46,000 --> 01:15:47,581
Leave it alone!

1009
01:15:48,544 --> 01:15:51,957
Poor kid. I bet she's alone in her room,
crying her eyes out.

1010
01:15:52,131 --> 01:15:54,622
-Who?
-Hermione, of course.

1011
01:15:54,800 --> 01:15:58,384
Come on, Harry, why do you think she
wouldn't tell us who she's coming with?

1012
01:15:58,554 --> 01:16:00,761
Because we'd take the mickey out of her
if she did.

1013
01:16:00,931 --> 01:16:06,016
Nobody asked her. Would've taken her
myself if she wasn't so bloody proud.

1014
01:16:06,979 --> 01:16:08,389
BOTH:
Hello, boys.

1015
01:16:08,564 --> 01:16:10,395
Don't you look...

1016
01:16:10,983 --> 01:16:12,143
...dashing.

1017
01:16:12,735 --> 01:16:15,898
There you are, Potter.
Are you and Miss Patil ready?

1018
01:16:16,072 --> 01:16:17,903
-Ready, professor?
-To dance.

1019
01:16:18,074 --> 01:16:21,111
It's traditional that the three champions--
Well, in this case, four.

1020
01:16:21,285 --> 01:16:22,320
--are the first to dance.

1021
01:16:22,661 --> 01:16:25,243
-Surely I told you that.
-No.

1022
01:16:25,456 --> 01:16:27,617
Oh, well, now you know.

1023
01:16:27,792 --> 01:16:29,123
Oh.

1024
01:16:29,627 --> 01:16:33,415
As for you, Mr. Weasley, you may proceed
into the Great Hall with Miss Patil.

1025
01:16:33,589 --> 01:16:35,921
-Oh, there you are.
-Come on, then.

1026
01:16:36,133 --> 01:16:37,669
McGONAGALL:
Come along this way.

1027
01:16:42,515 --> 01:16:44,346
Oh, come on.

1028
01:16:45,184 --> 01:16:46,219
Hi.

1029
01:16:46,393 --> 01:16:49,135
Now, I need you all to line up
in the procession, please.

1030
01:16:49,313 --> 01:16:50,723
Oh, you are very late.

1031
01:16:52,942 --> 01:16:55,354
This way. This way. Come along.

1032
01:16:57,029 --> 01:16:59,270
She looks beautiful!

1033
01:16:59,448 --> 01:17:01,029
Yeah, she does.

1034
01:17:24,974 --> 01:17:26,214
[GIGGLES]

1035
01:17:26,433 --> 01:17:28,515
[FANFARE PLAYING]

1036
01:17:48,414 --> 01:17:51,998
Is that Hermione Granger?
With Viktor Krum?

1037
01:17:52,626 --> 01:17:55,208
No. Absolutely not.

1038
01:17:59,925 --> 01:18:01,461
Hi!

1039
01:18:05,097 --> 01:18:06,132
[BATON TAPPING]

1040
01:18:10,227 --> 01:18:12,183
Harry, take my waist.

1041
01:18:13,105 --> 01:18:14,515
-What?
-Now!

1042
01:18:14,732 --> 01:18:16,814
[ORCHESTRA BEGINS PLAYING]

1043
01:18:35,211 --> 01:18:37,167
[CAT PURRS]

1044
01:18:54,521 --> 01:18:56,853
[HUMMING]

1045
01:19:05,783 --> 01:19:06,989
Ooh.

1046
01:19:21,131 --> 01:19:22,871
MAN:
Are you ready?!

1047
01:19:23,509 --> 01:19:25,716
[SINGING]
<i>Move your body like a hairy troll</i>

1048
01:19:26,553 --> 01:19:29,010
<i>Learning to rock and roll</i>

1049
01:19:29,431 --> 01:19:32,013
<i>Spin around like a crazy elf</i>

1050
01:19:32,518 --> 01:19:34,759
</i>Dancing by himself</i>

1051
01:19:35,062 --> 01:19:38,395
<i>Boogie down like a unicorn</i>

1052
01:19:38,565 --> 01:19:41,022
<i>No stopping till the break of dawn</i>

1053
01:19:41,193 --> 01:19:44,026
<i>Put your hands up in the air</i>

1054
01:19:44,196 --> 01:19:46,983
<i>Like an ogre who just don 't care</i>

1055
01:19:47,700 --> 01:19:50,362
<i>Can you dance like a Hippogriff?</i>

1056
01:19:52,705 --> 01:19:54,866
Ruddy pumpkinhead, isn't he?

1057
01:19:57,042 --> 01:20:00,455
I don't think it was the books
that had him going to the library.

1058
01:20:02,381 --> 01:20:03,917
May I have your arm?

1059
01:20:04,091 --> 01:20:06,798
Arm. Leg. I'm yours.

1060
01:20:32,745 --> 01:20:34,326
Hot, isn't it?

1061
01:20:34,997 --> 01:20:38,330
Viktor's gone to go and get drinks.
Would you care to join us?

1062
01:20:38,500 --> 01:20:42,163
No, we'd not care to join you and Viktor.

1063
01:20:43,881 --> 01:20:46,213
What's got your wand in a knot?

1064
01:20:46,508 --> 01:20:50,171
He's a Durmstrang.
You're fraternizing with the enemy.

1065
01:20:50,346 --> 01:20:53,930
The enemy?
Who was it wanting his autograph?

1066
01:20:54,641 --> 01:20:57,098
Besides, the whole point
of the tournament...

1067
01:20:57,269 --> 01:21:00,761
...is international
magical cooperation...

1068
01:21:01,357 --> 01:21:02,847
...to make friends.

1069
01:21:03,609 --> 01:21:06,772
I think he's got a bit more
than friendship on his mind.

1070
01:21:16,747 --> 01:21:19,079
Are you going to ask me
to dance or not?

1071
01:21:19,249 --> 01:21:20,659
No.

1072
01:21:28,926 --> 01:21:31,338
-He's using you.
-How dare you?!

1073
01:21:31,512 --> 01:21:35,721
-Besides, I can take care of myself.
-I doubt it. He's way too old.

1074
01:21:35,891 --> 01:21:39,554
-What?! What? That's what you think?
-Yeah, that's what I think.

1075
01:21:39,728 --> 01:21:41,844
You know the solution then, don't you?

1076
01:21:42,022 --> 01:21:44,013
-Go on.
-Next time there's a ball...

1077
01:21:44,191 --> 01:21:47,308
...pluck up the courage and ask me
before somebody else does!

1078
01:21:47,486 --> 01:21:49,522
And not as a last resort.

1079
01:21:49,696 --> 01:21:53,905
Well, that's-- I mean,
that's just completely off the point.

1080
01:21:54,076 --> 01:21:55,407
Harry.

1081
01:21:55,869 --> 01:21:57,154
Where have you been?

1082
01:21:57,329 --> 01:21:59,820
Never mind! Off to bed, both of you.

1083
01:22:00,374 --> 01:22:02,456
[MUSIC PLAYING IN BALLROOM]

1084
01:22:02,668 --> 01:22:06,661
-They get scary when they get older.
-Ron, you spoiled everything!

1085
01:22:06,839 --> 01:22:08,704
What's this about?

1086
01:22:10,217 --> 01:22:12,299
[SOBS]

1087
01:22:13,011 --> 01:22:16,003
SINGER:
<i>No, don't let</i>

1088
01:22:17,808 --> 01:22:22,142
<i>This magic die</i>

1089
01:22:23,897 --> 01:22:26,684
<i>The answer's there</i>

1090
01:22:28,360 --> 01:22:31,477
[BELL TOLLING]
[BIRDS CAWING]

1091
01:22:58,348 --> 01:23:00,430
[GRUNTING]

1092
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:27,082
VOLDEMORT:
Let me see it again.

1093
01:23:28,420 --> 01:23:31,287
Yes, the time is close now.

1094
01:23:36,011 --> 01:23:37,842
<i>Harry, at last!</i>

1095
01:23:39,181 --> 01:23:44,517
Step aside, Wormtail,
so I can give our guest a proper greeting.

1096
01:23:45,729 --> 01:23:47,185
[PANTING]

1097
01:23:47,397 --> 01:23:49,479
[FLOORBOARDS CREAKING]

1098
01:23:55,113 --> 01:23:56,523
You all right, Harry?

1099
01:23:57,950 --> 01:23:59,736
I just got in.

1100
01:24:00,327 --> 01:24:01,567
Me.

1101
01:24:06,375 --> 01:24:08,912
[HUMS]

1102
01:24:12,839 --> 01:24:16,127
HERMIONE: Harry, you told me
you'd figured the egg out weeks ago.

1103
01:24:16,301 --> 01:24:20,465
-The task is two days from now.
-Really? I had no idea.

1104
01:24:22,015 --> 01:24:23,801
I suppose Viktor's
already figured it out.

1105
01:24:23,976 --> 01:24:26,809
Wouldn't know. We don't actually
talk about the tournament.

1106
01:24:28,021 --> 01:24:32,640
Actually, we don't really talk at all.
Viktor's more of a physical being.

1107
01:24:33,777 --> 01:24:35,017
[LAUGHS]

1108
01:24:36,363 --> 01:24:39,571
I just mean he's not
particularly loquacious.

1109
01:24:39,741 --> 01:24:42,278
-Mm-hm.
-Mostly, he watches me study.

1110
01:24:43,078 --> 01:24:45,160
It's a bit annoying, actually.

1111
01:24:46,540 --> 01:24:49,247
You are trying to figure this egg out,
aren't you?

1112
01:24:50,085 --> 01:24:51,541
What's that supposed to mean?

1113
01:24:52,170 --> 01:24:55,162
It just means these tasks
are designed to test you...

1114
01:24:55,340 --> 01:24:58,503
...in the most brutal way.
They're almost cruel.

1115
01:24:59,678 --> 01:25:01,293
And...

1116
01:25:03,640 --> 01:25:05,505
...I'm scared for you.

1117
01:25:06,476 --> 01:25:09,058
You got by the dragons
mostly on nerve.

1118
01:25:09,688 --> 01:25:12,179
I'm not sure it's going
to be enough this time.

1119
01:25:12,357 --> 01:25:14,018
CEDRIC:
Hey, Potter!

1120
01:25:19,781 --> 01:25:21,271
-Potter!
HARRY: Cedric.

1121
01:25:23,994 --> 01:25:25,655
How--? How are you?

1122
01:25:26,705 --> 01:25:28,115
Spectacular.

1123
01:25:29,666 --> 01:25:33,500
I realize I never really thanked you properly
for tipping me off about those dragons.

1124
01:25:33,670 --> 01:25:35,956
Forget it. I'm sure you
would've done the same for me.

1125
01:25:36,298 --> 01:25:37,879
Exactly.

1126
01:25:38,967 --> 01:25:41,458
You know the Prefects' bathroom
on the fifth floor?

1127
01:25:45,390 --> 01:25:47,972
It's not a bad place for a bath.

1128
01:25:50,354 --> 01:25:52,219
Just take your egg...

1129
01:25:52,981 --> 01:25:55,723
...and mull things over
in the hot water.

1130
01:26:30,936 --> 01:26:33,097
I must be out of my mind.

1131
01:26:35,899 --> 01:26:38,311
[SCREECHING]

1132
01:26:43,281 --> 01:26:45,442
I'm definitely out of my mind.

1133
01:26:45,826 --> 01:26:47,782
[GIRL GIGGLING]

1134
01:26:48,120 --> 01:26:51,408
I'd try putting it in the water
if I were you.

1135
01:26:51,581 --> 01:26:53,446
Myrtle!

1136
01:26:53,625 --> 01:26:55,365
Hello, Harry.

1137
01:26:56,169 --> 01:26:59,377
Long time no see.

1138
01:26:59,548 --> 01:27:01,504
Oh.

1139
01:27:01,717 --> 01:27:03,423
[GIGGLING]

1140
01:27:03,635 --> 01:27:07,298
I was circling a blocked drain
the other day...

1141
01:27:07,472 --> 01:27:10,930
...and could swear I saw a bit
of Polyjuice Potion.

1142
01:27:11,101 --> 01:27:13,433
Not being a bad boy again,
are you, Harry?

1143
01:27:13,603 --> 01:27:15,343
Polyjuice Potion?

1144
01:27:16,148 --> 01:27:20,141
Kicked the habit. Myrtle, did you say,
"Try putting it in the water"?

1145
01:27:20,360 --> 01:27:23,227
[SQUEALS]

1146
01:27:23,864 --> 01:27:25,650
[COUGHING]

1147
01:27:26,992 --> 01:27:28,653
That's what he did.

1148
01:27:29,494 --> 01:27:31,155
The other boy...

1149
01:27:32,581 --> 01:27:34,663
...the handsome one...

1150
01:27:35,959 --> 01:27:37,290
...Cedric.

1151
01:27:40,589 --> 01:27:43,251
Well, go on. Open it.

1152
01:27:51,349 --> 01:27:56,343
WOMAN [SINGING]: <i>Come seek us
Where our voices sound</i>

1153
01:27:56,521 --> 01:28:01,185
<i>We cannot sing
Above the ground</i>

1154
01:28:01,359 --> 01:28:05,693
<i>An hour long you'll have to look</i>

1155
01:28:06,490 --> 01:28:11,154
<i>To recover what we took</i>

1156
01:28:12,245 --> 01:28:13,985
[COUGHING]

1157
01:28:17,209 --> 01:28:19,120
[MIMICS COUGHING]

1158
01:28:19,336 --> 01:28:20,826
Myrtle...

1159
01:28:22,214 --> 01:28:25,206
...there aren't merpeople
in the Black Lake, are there?

1160
01:28:25,383 --> 01:28:28,216
Oh, very good.

1161
01:28:29,095 --> 01:28:33,464
It took Cedric ages to riddle it out.

1162
01:28:33,975 --> 01:28:37,718
Almost all the bubbles were gone.

1163
01:28:40,065 --> 01:28:41,930
[GROWLS]

1164
01:28:42,150 --> 01:28:44,687
[GIGGLES]

1165
01:28:45,320 --> 01:28:48,027
[SQUEALING]

1166
01:28:49,908 --> 01:28:51,819
Oh, Harry.

1167
01:28:55,413 --> 01:28:57,369
Harry, tell me again.

1168
01:28:57,582 --> 01:28:58,867
[RON SNORING]

1169
01:28:59,084 --> 01:29:01,917
"Come seek us
where our voices sound."

1170
01:29:02,087 --> 01:29:05,329
The Black Lake, that's obvious.

1171
01:29:05,715 --> 01:29:08,127
"An hour long you'll have to look."

1172
01:29:08,301 --> 01:29:11,759
Again, obvious. Though, admittedly,
potentially problematic.

1173
01:29:13,139 --> 01:29:15,004
"Potentially problematic"?

1174
01:29:15,183 --> 01:29:18,425
When's the last time you held your breath
underwater for an hour, Hermione?

1175
01:29:18,979 --> 01:29:23,313
Look, Harry, we can do this.
The three of us can figure it out.

1176
01:29:23,483 --> 01:29:25,974
MOODY:
Hate to break up the skull session.

1177
01:29:26,152 --> 01:29:28,143
Professor McGonagall
wants you in her office.

1178
01:29:28,405 --> 01:29:30,771
Not you, Potter,
just Weasley and Granger.

1179
01:29:30,949 --> 01:29:33,611
But, sir, the second task
is only hours away, and--

1180
01:29:33,785 --> 01:29:36,401
Exactly. Presumably Potter
is well prepared by now...

1181
01:29:36,580 --> 01:29:38,445
...and could do with
a good night's sleep.

1182
01:29:38,623 --> 01:29:41,114
Go. Now!

1183
01:29:51,094 --> 01:29:52,880
Longbottom!

1184
01:29:53,054 --> 01:29:55,045
Why don't you help Potter
put his books back.

1185
01:30:03,732 --> 01:30:05,939
You know,
if you're interested in plants...

1186
01:30:06,109 --> 01:30:08,691
...you'd be better off with
Goshawk's Guide to Herbology.

1187
01:30:09,321 --> 01:30:13,610
Do you know there's a wizard in Nepal
who's growing gravity-resistant trees?

1188
01:30:13,783 --> 01:30:17,526
Neville, no offense,
but I really don't care...

1189
01:30:18,163 --> 01:30:19,869
...about plants.

1190
01:30:20,206 --> 01:30:21,912
Now, if there's...

1191
01:30:22,083 --> 01:30:26,873
...a Tibetan turnip that will allow me
to breathe underwater for an hour...

1192
01:30:27,047 --> 01:30:29,538
...then great. But otherwise--

1193
01:30:29,716 --> 01:30:33,504
I don't know about a turnip.
But you could always use gillyweed.

1194
01:30:34,888 --> 01:30:37,595
-Any bets? Any bets?
-Come on, place your bets!

1195
01:30:37,766 --> 01:30:39,222
Step up, mates! Don't be shy.

1196
01:30:39,392 --> 01:30:40,848
-Three lads.
-One lady.

1197
01:30:41,019 --> 01:30:43,180
-Four go down.
-But do four come up?

1198
01:30:43,355 --> 01:30:44,845
Don't be so mean.

1199
01:30:45,482 --> 01:30:47,268
-Any bets?
-Fleur's 10-1.

1200
01:30:49,402 --> 01:30:51,484
HARRY: You're sure about this, Neville?
-Absolutely.

1201
01:30:51,655 --> 01:30:53,566
HARRY: For an hour?
-Most likely.

1202
01:30:53,740 --> 01:30:55,230
Most likely?

1203
01:30:55,408 --> 01:30:57,615
Well, there is some debate
among herbologists...

1204
01:30:57,786 --> 01:31:00,243
...as to the effects of fresh water
versus salt water--

1205
01:31:00,413 --> 01:31:03,075
You're telling me this now?
You must be joking!

1206
01:31:03,249 --> 01:31:05,205
I just wanted to help.

1207
01:31:05,377 --> 01:31:08,494
Well, that makes you a right sight
better than Ron and Hermione.

1208
01:31:08,672 --> 01:31:10,412
Where are they anyway?

1209
01:31:10,590 --> 01:31:13,627
-You seem a little tense, Harry.
-Do l?

1210
01:31:20,642 --> 01:31:22,883
DUMBLEDORE:
<i>Welcome to the second task.</i>

1211
01:31:23,061 --> 01:31:26,724
<i>Last night, something was stolen
from each of our champions.</i>

1212
01:31:26,898 --> 01:31:28,263
<i>A treasure of sorts.</i>

1213
01:31:28,441 --> 01:31:31,057
<i>These four treasures,
one for each champion...</i>

1214
01:31:31,236 --> 01:31:33,943
<i>...now lie on the bottom
of the Black Lake.</i>

1215
01:31:34,114 --> 01:31:35,695
<i>In order to win...</i>

1216
01:31:35,865 --> 01:31:39,699
<i>...each champion need only find
their treasure and return to the surface.</i>

1217
01:31:39,869 --> 01:31:42,485
-<i>Simple enough, except for this:</i>
-Put that in your mouth.

1218
01:31:42,664 --> 01:31:46,282
<i>They will have but one hour to do so,
and one hour only.</i>

1219
01:31:46,459 --> 01:31:50,327
<i>After that, they'll be on their own.
No magic will save them.</i>

1220
01:31:50,880 --> 01:31:53,121
<i>You may begin
at the sound of the cannon.</i>

1221
01:31:55,385 --> 01:31:57,250
[CROWD CHEERING]

1222
01:32:04,436 --> 01:32:06,518
[GRUNTING]

1223
01:32:19,659 --> 01:32:22,617
-What's the matter with him?
-I don't know, I can't see him.

1224
01:32:23,955 --> 01:32:26,867
Oh, my God.
I've killed Harry Potter.

1225
01:32:28,793 --> 01:32:30,658
SEAMUS:
Yeah!

1226
01:32:31,838 --> 01:32:33,453
What?

1227
01:33:02,577 --> 01:33:07,116
[MERPEOPLE SINGING]

1228
01:33:16,341 --> 01:33:18,423
[WHOOSHING NOISE]

1229
01:33:30,313 --> 01:33:31,803
[GARBLED SQUEALING]

1230
01:33:31,981 --> 01:33:33,096
Oh!

1231
01:33:38,988 --> 01:33:40,774
[DISTORTED WAIL]

1232
01:33:53,002 --> 01:33:55,209
DUMBLEDORE: <i>The Beauxbatons
champion, Miss Delacour...</i>

1233
01:33:55,380 --> 01:33:57,871
<i>...has unfortunately
been forced to retire...</i>

1234
01:33:58,550 --> 01:34:01,633
<i>...so she will take no further part
in this task.</i>

1235
01:34:02,762 --> 01:34:05,595
[MERPEOPLE SINGING]

1236
01:34:19,070 --> 01:34:21,152
[MUFFLED WAILS ECHOING]

1237
01:34:55,565 --> 01:34:57,647
[SCREECHING]

1238
01:35:03,573 --> 01:35:05,063
[SCREECHES]

1239
01:35:19,464 --> 01:35:21,204
But she's my friend too!

1240
01:35:21,591 --> 01:35:22,671
[HISSES]

1241
01:35:22,842 --> 01:35:24,582
Only one!

1242
01:35:25,553 --> 01:35:27,339
[SHRIEKS]

1243
01:35:31,434 --> 01:35:33,299
[ROARING]

1244
01:36:07,387 --> 01:36:08,968
[GASPS]

1245
01:36:09,180 --> 01:36:11,262
[CROWD CHEERING]

1246
01:36:15,937 --> 01:36:17,802
Let's get down below.

1247
01:36:24,988 --> 01:36:27,650
[GASPING]

1248
01:36:27,865 --> 01:36:30,698
[CHANTING]
<i>Krum! Krum! Krum!</i>

1249
01:36:32,120 --> 01:36:33,735
[COUGHING]

1250
01:36:49,679 --> 01:36:51,294
[GRUNTING]

1251
01:36:54,600 --> 01:36:56,682
[SHRIEKING]

1252
01:37:21,919 --> 01:37:22,954
[CHIMES]

1253
01:37:23,171 --> 01:37:25,332
[GASPING AND COUGHING]

1254
01:37:28,176 --> 01:37:29,916
-Yes!
-Whoo!

1255
01:37:31,679 --> 01:37:34,842
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

1256
01:37:48,029 --> 01:37:50,111
<i>Ascendio!</i>

1257
01:37:55,328 --> 01:37:57,034
Harry!

1258
01:37:59,332 --> 01:38:00,788
He's all right.

1259
01:38:02,001 --> 01:38:03,457
He's all right. Barty!

1260
01:38:03,628 --> 01:38:07,041
SEAMUS: Go get him another towel.
-I want all the judges over here now!

1261
01:38:07,632 --> 01:38:11,090
You saved her, even though
she wasn't yours to save.

1262
01:38:11,803 --> 01:38:13,418
My little sister.

1263
01:38:13,888 --> 01:38:15,469
Thank you.

1264
01:38:16,265 --> 01:38:18,972
And you! You helped.

1265
01:38:19,644 --> 01:38:22,636
Well, yeah, a bit.

1266
01:38:24,690 --> 01:38:26,430
[SPEAKS IN FRENCH]

1267
01:38:28,111 --> 01:38:29,692
Merci.

1268
01:38:29,862 --> 01:38:31,022
-Harry!
-Hermione! Ow.

1269
01:38:31,197 --> 01:38:33,859
Are you all right? You must be freezing.

1270
01:38:35,118 --> 01:38:37,029
Personally, I think
you behaved admirably.

1271
01:38:37,203 --> 01:38:39,910
I finished last, Hermione. Ah!

1272
01:38:40,081 --> 01:38:44,199
Next to last.
Fleur never got past the Grindylows.

1273
01:38:44,377 --> 01:38:47,619
KARKAROFF:
Krum! Krum! Krum!

1274
01:38:47,797 --> 01:38:50,664
-Come on! Come on!
-Attention!

1275
01:38:53,010 --> 01:38:55,626
Attention!

1276
01:38:56,097 --> 01:38:59,965
The winner is Mr. Diggory...

1277
01:39:00,393 --> 01:39:03,885
...who showed innate command
of the Bubble-Head Charm.

1278
01:39:04,063 --> 01:39:06,725
However, seeing as Mr. Potter
would have finished first...

1279
01:39:06,899 --> 01:39:11,859
...had it not been for his determination
to rescue not only Mr. Weasley...

1280
01:39:12,029 --> 01:39:16,318
...but the others as well,
we've agreed to award him...

1281
01:39:16,492 --> 01:39:18,107
...second place...

1282
01:39:18,286 --> 01:39:20,117
-Yes!
-Second place!

1283
01:39:20,288 --> 01:39:22,950
...for outstanding moral fiber!

1284
01:39:24,208 --> 01:39:25,744
Yes!

1285
01:39:26,419 --> 01:39:27,534
Oh!

1286
01:39:29,422 --> 01:39:31,037
-Right on.
-All that moral fiber, eh?

1287
01:39:31,215 --> 01:39:32,876
-It's great.
-Moral fiber?

1288
01:39:33,050 --> 01:39:35,382
Blimey. Even when you go wrong,
it turns out right.

1289
01:39:35,553 --> 01:39:38,215
-Yeah, well done, Moral Fiber.
-Congratulations, Potter.

1290
01:39:38,389 --> 01:39:40,050
-A fine achievement.
-Thank you.

1291
01:39:40,224 --> 01:39:41,760
Well done, boy.

1292
01:39:41,934 --> 01:39:45,176
RON: See you at Hagrid's, Harry.
CROUCH: I'm sorry we haven't spoken.

1293
01:39:45,354 --> 01:39:49,347
After all, your story is one
I've heard so many times.

1294
01:39:50,359 --> 01:39:53,817
Quite remarkable, really.
Tragic, of course...

1295
01:39:53,988 --> 01:39:55,944
...to lose one's family.

1296
01:39:57,992 --> 01:40:00,153
Never whole again, are we?

1297
01:40:02,413 --> 01:40:04,449
Still, life goes on...

1298
01:40:05,166 --> 01:40:06,827
...and here we stand.

1299
01:40:09,754 --> 01:40:12,416
I'm sure your parents would be
very proud of you today, Potter.

1300
01:40:12,590 --> 01:40:14,080
Bartemius!

1301
01:40:14,258 --> 01:40:18,376
Not trying to lure Potter into one of the
Ministry's summer internships, are we?

1302
01:40:18,554 --> 01:40:21,967
The last boy who went into the
Department of Mysteries never came out!

1303
01:40:34,237 --> 01:40:36,102
And they say I'm mad.

1304
01:40:45,414 --> 01:40:49,123
Now, I remember--
I remember when I first met you all.

1305
01:40:49,293 --> 01:40:52,285
Biggest bunch of misfits
I ever set eyes on.

1306
01:40:52,838 --> 01:40:55,420
Suppose you remind me
of meself a little.

1307
01:40:55,591 --> 01:40:59,630
-And here we all are, four years later.
-We're still a bunch of misfits.

1308
01:40:59,804 --> 01:41:03,137
Well, maybe,
but we've all got each other.

1309
01:41:03,307 --> 01:41:04,843
And Harry, of course.

1310
01:41:05,017 --> 01:41:10,387
Soon to be the youngest
Triwizard champion there's ever been!

1311
01:41:10,606 --> 01:41:12,642
Hooray!

1312
01:41:14,068 --> 01:41:15,399
ALL [SINGING]:
Hogwarts, Hogwarts

1313
01:41:15,570 --> 01:41:16,730
Hoggy Warty Hogwarts

1314
01:41:16,904 --> 01:41:19,361
Teach us something, please

1315
01:41:19,532 --> 01:41:21,614
[GRUNTING]

1316
01:41:29,333 --> 01:41:30,823
HARRY:
Mr. Crouch?

1317
01:41:37,758 --> 01:41:39,339
DUMBLEDORE:
A man has died here, Fudge.

1318
01:41:39,510 --> 01:41:41,501
And he won't be the last.
You must take action.

1319
01:41:41,679 --> 01:41:43,260
FUDGE:
I will not.

1320
01:41:43,431 --> 01:41:47,515
In times like these, the wizard world looks
to its leaders for strength, Dumbledore!

1321
01:41:47,685 --> 01:41:49,050
DUMBLEDORE:
Then for once show them some!

1322
01:41:49,228 --> 01:41:53,267
The Triwizard Tournament will not be
canceled. I will not be seen as a coward!

1323
01:41:53,441 --> 01:41:56,649
DUMBLEDORE: A true leader does what
is right, no matter what others think.

1324
01:41:56,819 --> 01:41:59,606
-What did you say to me?
MOODY: Excuse me, gentlemen.

1325
01:41:59,780 --> 01:42:03,443
It may interest you to know
this conversation is no longer private.

1326
01:42:07,788 --> 01:42:09,369
Oh, Harry!

1327
01:42:09,540 --> 01:42:11,826
Harry, how good to see you again.

1328
01:42:12,668 --> 01:42:14,158
I can come back later, professor.

1329
01:42:14,337 --> 01:42:17,704
Not necessary, Harry. The minister and I
are done. I'll be back in a moment.

1330
01:42:17,882 --> 01:42:20,419
Minister, after you.

1331
01:42:20,968 --> 01:42:22,959
There you are. Your hat.

1332
01:42:23,137 --> 01:42:26,800
Oh, Harry, do feel free to indulge in
a little Licorice Snap in my absence.

1333
01:42:26,974 --> 01:42:30,137
But I have to warn you,
they're a wee bit sharp.

1334
01:42:56,337 --> 01:42:57,747
Aah!

1335
01:42:57,963 --> 01:43:00,045
[LICORICE SNAPS SQUEALING]

1336
01:43:04,261 --> 01:43:06,923
[RUMBLING]

1337
01:43:45,386 --> 01:43:47,047
[YELLING]

1338
01:43:53,102 --> 01:43:55,184
[GRUNTING AND PANTING]

1339
01:44:01,652 --> 01:44:03,233
Professor?

1340
01:44:03,404 --> 01:44:05,941
-Professor.
-Yeah.

1341
01:44:16,834 --> 01:44:20,622
Igor Karkaroff, you have been brought
from Azkaban at your own request...

1342
01:44:20,796 --> 01:44:22,707
...to present evidence to this council.

1343
01:44:22,882 --> 01:44:25,589
Should your testimony
prove consequential...

1344
01:44:25,760 --> 01:44:29,844
...council may be prepared
to order your immediate release.

1345
01:44:30,014 --> 01:44:34,599
Until such time, you remain in the eyes
of the Ministry a convicted Death Eater.

1346
01:44:34,769 --> 01:44:36,384
Do you accept these terms?

1347
01:44:37,021 --> 01:44:39,683
-I do, sir.
-And what do you wish to present?

1348
01:44:40,065 --> 01:44:42,522
I have names, sir.

1349
01:44:43,068 --> 01:44:46,686
There was Rosier, Evan Rosier.

1350
01:44:49,366 --> 01:44:51,857
-Rosier is dead.
-He took a piece of me with him...

1351
01:44:52,036 --> 01:44:54,152
-...though, didn't he?
KARKAROFF: I didn't know.

1352
01:44:54,371 --> 01:44:56,987
CROUCH: If that is all the witness has--
KARKAROFF: No, no, no.

1353
01:44:57,166 --> 01:45:00,454
There was Rookwood! He was a spy.

1354
01:45:00,628 --> 01:45:02,994
Augustus Rookwood?
Of the Department of Mysteries?

1355
01:45:03,172 --> 01:45:04,332
KARKAROFF:
Yeah, the same.

1356
01:45:04,507 --> 01:45:08,216
He passed information to You-Know-Who
from inside the Ministry itself.

1357
01:45:09,428 --> 01:45:12,716
Very well. Council will deliberate.

1358
01:45:12,890 --> 01:45:14,846
In the meantime,
you will return to Azkaban.

1359
01:45:15,017 --> 01:45:19,727
No! Wait, please! Please, I have more!
What about Snape? Severus Snape?

1360
01:45:19,897 --> 01:45:22,889
As the council is aware,
I've given evidence on this matter.

1361
01:45:23,067 --> 01:45:27,026
Severus Snape was indeed a Death Eater
and, prior to Lord Voldemort's downfall...

1362
01:45:27,196 --> 01:45:30,188
-...turned spy for us at great personal risk.
KARKAROFF: It's a lie!

1363
01:45:30,366 --> 01:45:33,824
-Today he's no more a Death Eater than l.
-Snape remains faithful to the Dark Lord!

1364
01:45:33,994 --> 01:45:36,235
Silence!

1365
01:45:36,872 --> 01:45:40,285
Unless the witness possesses
any genuine name of consequence...

1366
01:45:40,459 --> 01:45:42,575
...this session is now concluded.

1367
01:45:42,753 --> 01:45:44,789
Oh, no, no, no.

1368
01:45:45,756 --> 01:45:47,246
I've heard about one more.

1369
01:45:47,424 --> 01:45:49,961
CROUCH: What's that?
-The name.

1370
01:45:50,135 --> 01:45:51,591
-Yes?
-I know for a fact...

1371
01:45:51,762 --> 01:45:53,798
...this person took part
in the capture...

1372
01:45:53,973 --> 01:45:56,134
...and, by means
of the Cruciatus Curse...

1373
01:45:56,308 --> 01:45:59,800
...torture of the Auror Frank Longbottom
and his wife!

1374
01:45:59,979 --> 01:46:02,311
CROUCH: The name.
Give me the wretched name!

1375
01:46:02,481 --> 01:46:03,891
KARKAROFF:
Barty Crouch...

1376
01:46:04,108 --> 01:46:05,723
[GASPS]

1377
01:46:07,736 --> 01:46:08,771
...Junior.

1378
01:46:13,826 --> 01:46:15,487
[GRUNTS]

1379
01:46:18,247 --> 01:46:19,953
MAN:
Hold him down!

1380
01:46:23,586 --> 01:46:27,204
Get your filthy hands off me,
you pathetic little men!

1381
01:46:28,924 --> 01:46:30,505
Hello, Father.

1382
01:46:31,927 --> 01:46:33,963
You are no son of mine.

1383
01:46:35,931 --> 01:46:37,671
[YELLS]

1384
01:46:42,813 --> 01:46:44,519
[PANTING]

1385
01:46:45,316 --> 01:46:49,776
Curiosity is not a sin, Harry.
But you should exercise caution.

1386
01:46:51,155 --> 01:46:52,520
It's a Pensieve.

1387
01:46:52,698 --> 01:46:57,362
Very useful if, like me,
you find your mind a wee bit stretched.

1388
01:46:57,536 --> 01:47:01,074
It allows me to see once more
things I've already seen.

1389
01:47:01,540 --> 01:47:04,498
You see, Harry, I have searched
and searched for something...

1390
01:47:04,668 --> 01:47:06,249
...some small detail...

1391
01:47:07,671 --> 01:47:09,787
...something I might have overlooked...

1392
01:47:09,965 --> 01:47:14,174
...something that would explain why
these terrible things have happened.

1393
01:47:14,970 --> 01:47:18,838
Every time I get close to an answer,
it slips away.

1394
01:47:19,892 --> 01:47:21,507
It's maddening.

1395
01:47:23,896 --> 01:47:25,602
Sir? Mr. Crouch's son.

1396
01:47:26,357 --> 01:47:28,439
What exactly happened to him?

1397
01:47:28,609 --> 01:47:33,399
He was sent to Azkaban.
Destroyed Barty to do it.

1398
01:47:34,073 --> 01:47:37,691
But he had no choice.
The evidence was overwhelming.

1399
01:47:39,161 --> 01:47:42,119
-Why do you ask?
-It's just that l....

1400
01:47:42,873 --> 01:47:44,989
I had a dream about him.

1401
01:47:47,252 --> 01:47:50,039
It was in the summer, before school.

1402
01:47:52,216 --> 01:47:55,208
In the dream, I was in a house.

1403
01:47:55,386 --> 01:48:00,176
And Voldemort was there,
only he wasn't quite human.

1404
01:48:00,349 --> 01:48:03,967
And Wormtail was there too.
And Mr. Crouch's son.

1405
01:48:04,186 --> 01:48:06,222
DUMBLEDORE:
Have there been others like this dream?

1406
01:48:06,397 --> 01:48:09,639
Yes. Always the same one.

1407
01:48:12,695 --> 01:48:15,027
Sir, these dreams...

1408
01:48:15,197 --> 01:48:20,408
...what I see, you don't think
it's actually happening, do you?

1409
01:48:21,996 --> 01:48:24,988
I think it's unwise for you
to linger over these dreams, Harry.

1410
01:48:25,499 --> 01:48:27,455
I think it's best if you simply...

1411
01:48:33,090 --> 01:48:34,876
...cast them away.

1412
01:48:44,143 --> 01:48:45,553
KARKAROFF:
It's a sign, Severus.

1413
01:48:45,728 --> 01:48:46,763
[DOOR OPENING]

1414
01:48:46,937 --> 01:48:48,427
You know what it means as well as l.

1415
01:48:56,822 --> 01:48:58,028
Potter!

1416
01:48:58,198 --> 01:49:00,735
What's your hurry?

1417
01:49:05,831 --> 01:49:09,619
Congratulations, your performance
in the Black Lake was inspiring.

1418
01:49:09,793 --> 01:49:12,034
Gillyweed, am I correct?

1419
01:49:12,796 --> 01:49:14,332
Yes, sir.

1420
01:49:15,299 --> 01:49:16,664
Ingenious.

1421
01:49:18,510 --> 01:49:22,469
A rather rare herb, gillyweed.

1422
01:49:23,307 --> 01:49:26,799
Not something found
in your everyday garden.

1423
01:49:28,479 --> 01:49:30,435
Nor is this.

1424
01:49:34,651 --> 01:49:36,312
Know what it is?

1425
01:49:37,613 --> 01:49:39,023
Bubble juice, sir?

1426
01:49:39,615 --> 01:49:41,480
Veritaserum.

1427
01:49:42,242 --> 01:49:45,951
Three drops of this and You-Know-Who
himself would spill his darkest secrets.

1428
01:49:46,121 --> 01:49:51,286
The use of it on a student is,
regrettably, forbidden. However...

1429
01:49:51,960 --> 01:49:54,997
...should you ever steal
from my personal stores again...

1430
01:49:55,172 --> 01:50:00,007
...my hand might just slip over
your morning pumpkin juice.

1431
01:50:00,177 --> 01:50:04,591
-I haven't stolen anything.
-Don't lie to me.

1432
01:50:05,724 --> 01:50:11,435
Gillyweed may be innocuous,
but boomslang skin, lacewing flies?

1433
01:50:12,147 --> 01:50:15,480
You and your little friends are brewing
Polyjuice Potion, and believe me...

1434
01:50:15,651 --> 01:50:17,858
...I'm going to find out why!

1435
01:50:19,404 --> 01:50:20,610
[CHEERING]

1436
01:50:20,781 --> 01:50:22,646
[MARCHING BAND PLAYING]

1437
01:50:39,341 --> 01:50:41,423
[CHANTING IN FRENCH]

1438
01:50:44,680 --> 01:50:46,261
-Yeah!
-Yeah!

1439
01:51:05,450 --> 01:51:06,986
<i>Sonorus!</i>

1440
01:51:08,203 --> 01:51:10,285
[MUSIC STOPS]

1441
01:51:11,248 --> 01:51:16,584
Earlier today, Professor Moody placed
the Triwizard Cup deep within the maze.

1442
01:51:16,753 --> 01:51:21,713
Only he knows its exact position.
Now, as Mr. Diggory...

1443
01:51:21,925 --> 01:51:23,586
[CHEERING]

1444
01:51:23,802 --> 01:51:25,588
...and Mr. Potter...

1445
01:51:25,804 --> 01:51:27,260
[CHEERING]

1446
01:51:27,472 --> 01:51:29,212
...are tied for first position...

1447
01:51:29,391 --> 01:51:33,179
...they will be the first to enter the maze,
followed by Mr. Krum...

1448
01:51:33,353 --> 01:51:34,559
[CHEERING]

1449
01:51:34,771 --> 01:51:38,229
-...and Miss Delacour.
-Come on! Krum! Krum! Krum!

1450
01:51:39,151 --> 01:51:42,188
DUMBLEDORE: The first person
to touch the cup will be the winner!

1451
01:51:46,533 --> 01:51:49,275
I've instructed the staff
to patrol the perimeter.

1452
01:51:49,453 --> 01:51:52,365
Should, at any point, a contestant wish
to withdraw from the task...

1453
01:51:52,539 --> 01:51:57,033
...he or she need only send up
red sparks with their wands.

1454
01:51:57,377 --> 01:52:01,290
Contestants! Gather around. Quickly!

1455
01:52:04,426 --> 01:52:08,760
In the maze, you'll find no dragons
or creatures of the deep.

1456
01:52:08,931 --> 01:52:12,298
Instead, you'll face something
even more challenging.

1457
01:52:12,476 --> 01:52:15,468
You see, people change in the maze.

1458
01:52:15,646 --> 01:52:17,352
Oh, find the cup if you can.

1459
01:52:17,522 --> 01:52:22,312
But be very wary, you could just
lose yourselves along the way.

1460
01:52:23,779 --> 01:52:26,771
Champions, prepare yourselves!

1461
01:52:35,832 --> 01:52:37,288
Good luck.

1462
01:52:37,668 --> 01:52:39,624
-My boy.
-See you later, Dad.

1463
01:52:42,005 --> 01:52:44,587
On the count of three. One--

1464
01:52:46,635 --> 01:52:48,717
[MARCHING BAND PLAYING]

1465
01:54:20,103 --> 01:54:21,718
[CRASHING]

1466
01:54:21,938 --> 01:54:24,020
[PANTING]

1467
01:54:42,334 --> 01:54:44,541
[RUSTLING]

1468
01:54:52,719 --> 01:54:54,801
[PANTING]

1469
01:55:10,612 --> 01:55:11,772
[HISSING]

1470
01:55:11,947 --> 01:55:13,858
[SCREAMS]

1471
01:55:18,745 --> 01:55:20,610
[CREAKING]

1472
01:56:12,382 --> 01:56:13,588
Fleur?

1473
01:56:15,260 --> 01:56:16,716
Fleur.

1474
01:56:20,265 --> 01:56:22,096
<i>Periculum!</i>

1475
01:56:31,359 --> 01:56:33,941
[WIND HOWLING]

1476
01:56:50,045 --> 01:56:53,128
[VOICES WHISPERING]

1477
01:56:58,887 --> 01:57:00,593
[KRUM SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY]

1478
01:57:00,764 --> 01:57:02,254
CEDRIC:
Get down!

1479
01:57:02,807 --> 01:57:04,547
Get down!

1480
01:57:05,185 --> 01:57:06,425
<i>Expelliarmus!</i>

1481
01:57:09,898 --> 01:57:11,980
[GRUNTS]

1482
01:57:16,029 --> 01:57:19,237
No, don't! Stop!
He's bewitched, Cedric!

1483
01:57:19,407 --> 01:57:21,443
-Get off me!
-He's bewitched!

1484
01:57:28,625 --> 01:57:30,081
[SHIRT RIPS]
[GRUNTS]

1485
01:57:33,129 --> 01:57:34,790
HARRY:
Yes.

1486
01:57:37,259 --> 01:57:39,671
[GRUNTING]

1487
01:57:44,599 --> 01:57:46,339
[YELLS]

1488
01:57:55,652 --> 01:57:57,438
Harry!

1489
01:57:59,781 --> 01:58:01,396
Harry!

1490
01:58:03,785 --> 01:58:05,195
Harry!

1491
01:58:07,664 --> 01:58:09,245
Harry!

1492
01:58:11,251 --> 01:58:12,991
<i>Reducto!</i>

1493
01:58:23,471 --> 01:58:25,211
[PANTING]

1494
01:58:25,390 --> 01:58:27,255
[COUGHING]

1495
01:58:28,685 --> 01:58:32,303
-Th-- Thanks.
-No problem.

1496
01:58:32,689 --> 01:58:37,399
You know, for a moment there,
I thought you were gonna let it get me.

1497
01:58:37,569 --> 01:58:39,309
For a moment, so did l.

1498
01:58:41,197 --> 01:58:42,357
Some game, huh?

1499
01:58:43,366 --> 01:58:44,776
Some game.

1500
01:58:44,993 --> 01:58:46,949
[BRANCHES POPPING AND CRACKING]

1501
01:58:47,537 --> 01:58:49,619
[WIND HOWLING]

1502
01:58:50,206 --> 01:58:51,867
Go!

1503
01:59:02,010 --> 01:59:05,047
Go on, take it.
You saved me, take it!

1504
01:59:05,221 --> 01:59:07,212
-Together. One, two...
-Two...

1505
01:59:07,390 --> 01:59:08,596
-...three!
-...three!

1506
01:59:11,728 --> 01:59:13,889
[GRUNTING]

1507
01:59:21,112 --> 01:59:23,979
-You okay?
-Yeah. You?

1508
01:59:31,081 --> 01:59:32,412
Where are we?

1509
01:59:33,333 --> 01:59:35,415
[CROW CAWS]

1510
01:59:38,088 --> 01:59:39,749
I've been here before.

1511
01:59:43,385 --> 01:59:44,966
It's a Portkey.

1512
01:59:46,805 --> 01:59:51,014
-Harry, the cup is a Portkey.
-I've been here before, in a dream.

1513
01:59:53,103 --> 01:59:56,470
Cedric! We have to get back
to the cup. Now!

1514
01:59:56,648 --> 01:59:58,513
What are you talking about?

1515
01:59:58,692 --> 01:59:59,727
[DOOR CREAKING OPEN]

1516
02:00:00,819 --> 02:00:01,899
[HARRY YELLS]

1517
02:00:02,112 --> 02:00:03,648
[GRUNTING]

1518
02:00:03,863 --> 02:00:06,775
-Harry! What is it?
-Get back to the cup!

1519
02:00:14,416 --> 02:00:16,748
-Who are you? What do you want?
VOLDEMORT: Kill the spare.

1520
02:00:16,918 --> 02:00:19,660
-<i>Avada Kedavra!</i>
-No! Cedric!

1521
02:00:24,384 --> 02:00:26,796
[GRUNTING]

1522
02:00:30,974 --> 02:00:32,839
Do it! Now!

1523
02:00:37,981 --> 02:00:39,562
[GRUNTS]

1524
02:00:44,821 --> 02:00:47,312
Bone of the father...

1525
02:00:47,490 --> 02:00:49,776
...unwillingly given.

1526
02:00:57,250 --> 02:01:00,287
Flesh of the servant...

1527
02:01:02,338 --> 02:01:05,501
...willingly sacrificed.

1528
02:01:06,050 --> 02:01:08,416
[WORMTAIL YELLS]

1529
02:01:09,596 --> 02:01:13,339
And blood of the enemy...

1530
02:01:17,187 --> 02:01:18,973
[GRUNTING]

1531
02:01:19,147 --> 02:01:23,015
-...forcibly taken.
-Oh! Aah! Aah!

1532
02:01:23,234 --> 02:01:24,849
[GRUNTING]

1533
02:01:27,697 --> 02:01:30,655
The Dark Lord shall rise...

1534
02:01:31,409 --> 02:01:33,365
-...again.
-Aah!

1535
02:01:34,078 --> 02:01:36,160
[HARRY YELLING]

1536
02:01:45,757 --> 02:01:47,839
[WIND HOWLING]

1537
02:01:56,643 --> 02:02:00,807
[HARRY GRUNTING]

1538
02:02:07,028 --> 02:02:09,110
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

1539
02:02:30,385 --> 02:02:31,841
[CHUCKLES]

1540
02:02:36,766 --> 02:02:40,133
My wand, Wormtail.

1541
02:02:49,696 --> 02:02:51,652
Hold out your arm.

1542
02:02:51,823 --> 02:02:53,438
Master.

1543
02:02:53,616 --> 02:02:56,232
Thank you, master.

1544
02:02:56,411 --> 02:02:57,867
The other arm, Wormtail.

1545
02:03:11,759 --> 02:03:13,841
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1546
02:03:16,681 --> 02:03:18,763
[HOWLING AND MOANING]

1547
02:03:38,494 --> 02:03:40,405
Welcome, my friends.

1548
02:03:41,831 --> 02:03:44,573
Thirteen years it's been, and yet...

1549
02:03:45,209 --> 02:03:50,704
...here you stand before me
as though it were only yesterday.

1550
02:03:51,674 --> 02:03:54,586
I confess myself...

1551
02:03:55,053 --> 02:03:56,634
...disappointed.

1552
02:03:57,305 --> 02:03:59,387
Not one of you tried to find me.

1553
02:03:59,557 --> 02:04:02,924
Crabbe! Macnair!

1554
02:04:03,853 --> 02:04:05,184
Goyle!

1555
02:04:07,690 --> 02:04:09,305
Not even you...

1556
02:04:13,196 --> 02:04:15,107
...Lucius.

1557
02:04:16,950 --> 02:04:21,785
My Lord, had I detected any sign,
a whisper of your whereabouts--

1558
02:04:21,955 --> 02:04:24,947
There were signs, my slippery friend.
And more than whispers.

1559
02:04:25,124 --> 02:04:30,289
I assure you, my Lord,
I have never renounced the old ways.

1560
02:04:32,006 --> 02:04:37,626
The face I have been obliged to present
each day since your absence...

1561
02:04:39,639 --> 02:04:42,255
...that is my true mask.

1562
02:04:42,642 --> 02:04:44,223
I returned.

1563
02:04:44,978 --> 02:04:46,468
[GASPS]

1564
02:04:46,688 --> 02:04:50,556
Out of fear, not loyalty.

1565
02:04:51,734 --> 02:04:57,479
Still, you have proved yourself useful
these past few months, Wormtail.

1566
02:05:02,704 --> 02:05:05,036
Thank you, master.

1567
02:05:05,623 --> 02:05:07,363
Thank you.

1568
02:05:08,126 --> 02:05:10,287
VOLDEMORT:
Oh. Tsk, tsk, tsk.

1569
02:05:10,461 --> 02:05:12,827
-Such a handsome boy.
HARRY: Don't touch him!

1570
02:05:14,298 --> 02:05:15,788
VOLDEMORT:
Harry.

1571
02:05:15,967 --> 02:05:18,754
I'd almost forgotten you were here.

1572
02:05:18,928 --> 02:05:23,342
Standing on the bones
of my father. Yeah.

1573
02:05:23,516 --> 02:05:24,881
I'd introduce you...

1574
02:05:25,059 --> 02:05:29,348
...but word has it you're almost
as famous as me these days.

1575
02:05:32,025 --> 02:05:34,687
The boy who lived.

1576
02:05:34,861 --> 02:05:37,773
How lies have fed your legend, Harry.

1577
02:05:37,947 --> 02:05:41,940
Shall I reveal what really happened
that night 13 years ago?

1578
02:05:42,118 --> 02:05:46,828
Shall I divulge how
I truly lost my powers?

1579
02:05:46,998 --> 02:05:48,488
Yes, shall I?

1580
02:05:48,958 --> 02:05:50,289
It was love.

1581
02:05:50,460 --> 02:05:54,954
You see, when dear, sweet Lily Potter
gave her life for her only son...

1582
02:05:55,131 --> 02:05:57,713
...she provided the ultimate protection.

1583
02:05:58,134 --> 02:05:59,920
I could not touch him.

1584
02:06:01,137 --> 02:06:03,298
It was old magic.

1585
02:06:03,473 --> 02:06:05,714
Something I should have foreseen.

1586
02:06:05,892 --> 02:06:07,678
But no matter, no matter.

1587
02:06:07,852 --> 02:06:10,059
Things have changed.

1588
02:06:10,813 --> 02:06:14,305
I can touch you...

1589
02:06:14,942 --> 02:06:16,648
...now.

1590
02:06:17,278 --> 02:06:19,360
[SCREAMING]

1591
02:06:21,324 --> 02:06:23,280
[MOANING]

1592
02:06:24,827 --> 02:06:26,158
Yeah.

1593
02:06:27,872 --> 02:06:29,328
[YELLS]

1594
02:06:32,502 --> 02:06:36,165
Astonishing what a few drops
of your blood will do, eh, Harry?

1595
02:06:37,381 --> 02:06:39,042
Pick up your wand, Potter.

1596
02:06:40,676 --> 02:06:42,883
I said, pick it up! Get up! Get up!

1597
02:06:44,514 --> 02:06:46,800
You've been taught how to duel,
I presume, yes?

1598
02:06:46,974 --> 02:06:49,386
First, we bow to each other.

1599
02:06:49,560 --> 02:06:51,972
Come on, now, Harry.
The niceties must be observed.

1600
02:06:52,146 --> 02:06:55,354
Dumbledore wouldn't want you
to forget your manners, would he?

1601
02:06:55,525 --> 02:06:56,856
I said, bow.

1602
02:06:57,026 --> 02:06:58,482
[GRUNTS]

1603
02:06:58,694 --> 02:07:03,028
-That's better. And now....
-No.

1604
02:07:03,449 --> 02:07:05,314
<i>Crucio!</i>

1605
02:07:07,787 --> 02:07:09,527
<i>Crucio!</i>

1606
02:07:10,581 --> 02:07:12,537
Attaboy, Harry.

1607
02:07:12,708 --> 02:07:14,824
Your parents would be proud.

1608
02:07:15,128 --> 02:07:18,541
Especially your filthy Muggle mother.

1609
02:07:18,714 --> 02:07:20,295
<i>Expelliar--</i>

1610
02:07:23,302 --> 02:07:25,714
I'm going to kill you, Harry Potter.

1611
02:07:25,888 --> 02:07:27,879
I'm going to destroy you.

1612
02:07:30,059 --> 02:07:35,645
After tonight, no one will ever again
question my powers.

1613
02:07:36,274 --> 02:07:38,856
After tonight, if they speak of you...

1614
02:07:39,026 --> 02:07:41,688
...they'll speak only of how you...

1615
02:07:41,988 --> 02:07:43,819
...begged for death.

1616
02:07:43,990 --> 02:07:47,733
And l, being a merciful Lord...

1617
02:07:48,286 --> 02:07:49,901
...obliged.

1618
02:07:50,246 --> 02:07:51,736
Get up!

1619
02:07:51,956 --> 02:07:54,038
[GRUNTING]

1620
02:07:56,752 --> 02:07:58,708
Don't you turn your back on me,
Harry Potter!

1621
02:07:58,880 --> 02:08:01,121
I want you to look at me
when I kill you!

1622
02:08:01,299 --> 02:08:04,507
I want to see the light
leave your eyes!

1623
02:08:08,556 --> 02:08:10,012
[GRUNTS]

1624
02:08:10,183 --> 02:08:12,265
[PANTING]

1625
02:08:18,441 --> 02:08:20,181
Have it your way.

1626
02:08:21,235 --> 02:08:23,601
-<i>Expelliarmus!</i>
-<i>Avada Kedavra!</i>

1627
02:08:41,130 --> 02:08:43,792
Do nothing! He's mine to finish!

1628
02:08:44,008 --> 02:08:45,498
[GRUNTING]

1629
02:08:48,387 --> 02:08:50,093
He's mine!

1630
02:08:50,514 --> 02:08:51,970
[GRUNTS]

1631
02:08:58,105 --> 02:08:59,561
[GROANS]

1632
02:09:23,172 --> 02:09:27,165
Harry, when the connection is broken,
you must get to the Portkey.

1633
02:09:27,343 --> 02:09:29,379
We can linger for a moment
to give you some time...

1634
02:09:29,553 --> 02:09:31,339
...but only a moment.
Do you understand?

1635
02:09:32,515 --> 02:09:35,552
CEDRIC:
Harry, take my body back, will you?

1636
02:09:35,726 --> 02:09:38,263
Take my body back to my father.

1637
02:09:39,313 --> 02:09:40,644
Let go.

1638
02:09:41,107 --> 02:09:43,063
Sweetheart, you're ready.

1639
02:09:43,901 --> 02:09:46,517
Let go! Let go!

1640
02:09:52,285 --> 02:09:53,650
<i>Accio!</i>

1641
02:09:59,375 --> 02:10:01,366
No!

1642
02:10:01,794 --> 02:10:03,250
[CROWD CHEERING]

1643
02:10:05,840 --> 02:10:07,796
[MARCHING BAND PLAYING]
[SOBBING]

1644
02:10:14,098 --> 02:10:15,713
AMOS:
He did it!

1645
02:10:15,933 --> 02:10:16,968
[SCREAMS]

1646
02:10:17,143 --> 02:10:18,599
DUMBLEDORE:
Harry!

1647
02:10:21,397 --> 02:10:22,887
Harry!

1648
02:10:24,066 --> 02:10:27,308
No! No! No, don't!

1649
02:10:27,611 --> 02:10:29,476
For God's sake, Dumbledore,
what's happened?

1650
02:10:29,780 --> 02:10:32,362
He's back. He's back.

1651
02:10:32,533 --> 02:10:34,569
Voldemort's back.

1652
02:10:34,744 --> 02:10:37,110
Cedric, he asked me
to bring his body back.

1653
02:10:37,288 --> 02:10:39,620
I couldn't leave him, not there.

1654
02:10:39,790 --> 02:10:42,577
It's all right, Harry. It's all right.

1655
02:10:42,752 --> 02:10:45,084
He's home. You both are.

1656
02:10:45,254 --> 02:10:48,872
Keep everybody in their seats.
A boy has just been killed.

1657
02:10:51,927 --> 02:10:55,545
The body must be moved, Dumbledore.
There are too many people.

1658
02:10:55,890 --> 02:10:57,596
Let me through.

1659
02:10:57,767 --> 02:10:59,257
Let me through!

1660
02:11:01,187 --> 02:11:02,427
Let me through!

1661
02:11:02,605 --> 02:11:04,015
That's my son!

1662
02:11:05,316 --> 02:11:06,772
That's my boy!

1663
02:11:09,612 --> 02:11:12,319
It's my boy!

1664
02:11:13,074 --> 02:11:14,530
[SOBS]

1665
02:11:15,117 --> 02:11:18,701
-Come on. Get up. Easy, easy!
-No.

1666
02:11:18,871 --> 02:11:21,829
This is not where you want to be
right now. Come on.

1667
02:11:22,500 --> 02:11:24,707
No!

1668
02:11:27,797 --> 02:11:30,163
It's all right, I got you.

1669
02:11:30,341 --> 02:11:33,674
I got you. Come on. Easy, now.

1670
02:11:37,681 --> 02:11:39,467
AMOS:
No!

1671
02:11:40,601 --> 02:11:42,466
No!

1672
02:12:24,854 --> 02:12:26,560
Are you all right, Potter?

1673
02:12:27,148 --> 02:12:29,059
Does it hurt? That?

1674
02:12:29,233 --> 02:12:31,019
Not so much now.

1675
02:12:31,986 --> 02:12:34,068
Perhaps I'd better take a look at it.

1676
02:12:37,199 --> 02:12:39,190
HARRY:
The cup was a Portkey.

1677
02:12:41,912 --> 02:12:43,743
Someone had bewitched it.

1678
02:12:44,039 --> 02:12:46,121
What was it like?

1679
02:12:46,459 --> 02:12:48,120
-What was he like?
-Who?

1680
02:12:48,294 --> 02:12:50,034
The Dark Lord.

1681
02:12:50,463 --> 02:12:51,873
HARRY:
Aah!

1682
02:12:52,381 --> 02:12:55,464
What was it like
to stand in his presence?

1683
02:12:56,719 --> 02:12:58,550
I don't know.

1684
02:12:59,054 --> 02:13:01,215
[GRUNTING]

1685
02:13:01,390 --> 02:13:04,302
It was like I'd fallen
into one of my dreams...

1686
02:13:07,271 --> 02:13:09,262
...into one of my nightmares.

1687
02:13:23,662 --> 02:13:25,118
[GASPS]

1688
02:13:28,000 --> 02:13:29,581
Were there others?

1689
02:13:29,752 --> 02:13:31,538
In the graveyard, were there others?

1690
02:13:31,712 --> 02:13:33,293
Um....

1691
02:13:35,925 --> 02:13:37,335
I....

1692
02:13:38,052 --> 02:13:41,965
I don't think I said anything
about a graveyard, professor.

1693
02:13:49,396 --> 02:13:52,684
[IMITATING HAGRID] "Marvelous
creatures, dragons, aren't they? "

1694
02:13:57,112 --> 02:14:00,149
Did you think that oaf
would've led you into the woods...

1695
02:14:00,324 --> 02:14:02,235
...if I hadn't suggested it?

1696
02:14:02,660 --> 02:14:04,742
[BOTTLES CLANKING]

1697
02:14:05,788 --> 02:14:09,451
Do you think Cedric Diggory would've
told you to open the egg underwater...

1698
02:14:09,625 --> 02:14:12,116
...if I hadn't told him first myself?

1699
02:14:13,754 --> 02:14:16,416
Did you think Neville Longbottom,
the witless wonder...

1700
02:14:16,590 --> 02:14:19,798
...could've provided you with gillyweed
if I hadn't given him the book...

1701
02:14:19,969 --> 02:14:21,505
...that led him straight to it? Huh?

1702
02:14:23,556 --> 02:14:25,012
Eh?

1703
02:14:29,937 --> 02:14:33,930
It was you from the beginning.
You put my name in the Goblet of Fire.

1704
02:14:34,483 --> 02:14:36,144
You bewitched Krum, but you--

1705
02:14:36,318 --> 02:14:38,149
[MOCKING]
"But-- But--"

1706
02:14:38,320 --> 02:14:40,481
You won because I made it so, Potter.

1707
02:14:41,115 --> 02:14:44,607
You ended up in that graveyard tonight
because it was meant to be so.

1708
02:14:44,785 --> 02:14:46,070
And now the deed is done.

1709
02:14:46,287 --> 02:14:47,322
[HARRY GRUNTS]

1710
02:14:47,746 --> 02:14:52,080
The blood that runs through these veins
runs within the Dark Lord.

1711
02:14:55,212 --> 02:14:57,043
[SIGHS AND SPITS]

1712
02:15:00,593 --> 02:15:04,085
Imagine how he will reward me
when he learns...

1713
02:15:05,014 --> 02:15:07,505
...that I have once and for all...

1714
02:15:08,142 --> 02:15:12,476
...silenced the great Harry Potter.

1715
02:15:12,646 --> 02:15:13,886
DUMBLEDORE:
<i>Expelliarmus!</i>

1716
02:15:18,611 --> 02:15:19,851
Severus.

1717
02:15:21,739 --> 02:15:22,819
[GASPING]

1718
02:15:22,990 --> 02:15:24,776
DUMBLEDORE:
That's it, take it.

1719
02:15:25,826 --> 02:15:29,284
-Do you know who I am?
-Albus Dumbledore.

1720
02:15:29,455 --> 02:15:32,162
-Are you Alastor Moody? Are you?
-No.

1721
02:15:32,333 --> 02:15:35,416
Is he in this room? Is he in this room?

1722
02:15:38,464 --> 02:15:40,000
Harry, away from there!

1723
02:16:00,986 --> 02:16:04,319
DUMBLEDORE: You all right, Alastor?
-I'm sorry, Albus.

1724
02:16:05,282 --> 02:16:07,364
That's Moody. But then who's--?

1725
02:16:07,534 --> 02:16:08,899
[SNIFFS]

1726
02:16:09,161 --> 02:16:10,241
Polyjuice Potion.

1727
02:16:10,412 --> 02:16:13,654
Now we know who's been stealing
from your stores, Severus.

1728
02:16:13,916 --> 02:16:15,326
We'll get you up in a minute.

1729
02:16:15,501 --> 02:16:17,037
[GROANS]

1730
02:16:17,252 --> 02:16:19,163
[GURGLING]

1731
02:16:23,550 --> 02:16:25,632
[GRUNTING AND GAGGING]

1732
02:16:33,310 --> 02:16:35,847
[SCREAMS]

1733
02:16:49,743 --> 02:16:51,654
-Aah!
-Harry!

1734
02:16:55,207 --> 02:16:57,539
Barty Crouch Junior.

1735
02:16:57,793 --> 02:17:00,705
I'll show you mine
if you show me yours.

1736
02:17:03,090 --> 02:17:04,296
Your arm, Harry.

1737
02:17:08,637 --> 02:17:10,878
CROUCH JUNIOR:
You know what this means, don't you?

1738
02:17:11,807 --> 02:17:13,138
He's back.

1739
02:17:14,309 --> 02:17:16,470
Lord Voldemort has returned.

1740
02:17:17,396 --> 02:17:19,728
I'm sorry, sir. I couldn't help it.

1741
02:17:19,940 --> 02:17:24,479
Send an owl to Azkaban. I think
they'll find they're missing a prisoner.

1742
02:17:24,945 --> 02:17:27,436
-I'll be welcomed back like a hero.
DUMBLEDORE: Perhaps.

1743
02:17:27,990 --> 02:17:30,857
Personally, I've never had much time
for heroes.

1744
02:17:41,837 --> 02:17:43,919
[OWL HOOTING]

1745
02:17:50,763 --> 02:17:53,425
Today, we acknowledge...

1746
02:17:54,141 --> 02:17:56,883
...a really terrible loss.

1747
02:17:59,021 --> 02:18:01,763
Cedric Diggory was, as you all know...

1748
02:18:01,940 --> 02:18:04,272
...exceptionally hard-working...

1749
02:18:05,235 --> 02:18:07,521
...infinitely fair-minded...

1750
02:18:08,113 --> 02:18:10,399
...and, most importantly...

1751
02:18:10,699 --> 02:18:15,284
...a fierce, fierce friend.

1752
02:18:16,413 --> 02:18:20,782
Now, I think, therefore, you have
the right to know exactly how he died.

1753
02:18:23,837 --> 02:18:25,373
You see...

1754
02:18:26,215 --> 02:18:28,297
...Cedric Diggory was murdered...

1755
02:18:29,218 --> 02:18:31,209
...by Lord Voldemort!

1756
02:18:33,096 --> 02:18:36,680
The Ministry of Magic
does not wish me to tell you this.

1757
02:18:37,309 --> 02:18:41,018
But not to do so, I think,
would be an insult to his memory.

1758
02:18:43,190 --> 02:18:44,851
Now, the pain...

1759
02:18:45,025 --> 02:18:48,688
...we all feel at this dreadful loss
reminds me...

1760
02:18:48,862 --> 02:18:50,193
...and reminds us...

1761
02:18:50,364 --> 02:18:54,073
...that while we may come from different
places and speak in different tongues...

1762
02:18:54,243 --> 02:18:57,656
...our hearts beat as one.

1763
02:18:58,163 --> 02:19:00,199
In light of recent events...

1764
02:19:00,541 --> 02:19:05,456
...the bonds of friendship we've made
this year will be more important than ever.

1765
02:19:06,338 --> 02:19:11,674
Remember that, and Cedric Diggory
will not have died in vain.

1766
02:19:12,094 --> 02:19:14,255
You remember that...

1767
02:19:14,847 --> 02:19:17,884
...and we'll celebrate a boy who was...

1768
02:19:18,433 --> 02:19:20,890
...kind and honest...

1769
02:19:21,395 --> 02:19:25,980
...and brave and true,
right to the very end.

1770
02:19:51,216 --> 02:19:53,252
I never liked these curtains.

1771
02:19:53,844 --> 02:19:56,506
Set them on fire in my fourth year.

1772
02:19:56,847 --> 02:19:58,678
By accident, of course.

1773
02:20:04,354 --> 02:20:08,723
I put you in terrible danger
this year, Harry. I'm sorry.

1774
02:20:12,154 --> 02:20:13,815
Professor...

1775
02:20:14,031 --> 02:20:17,023
...when I was in the graveyard,
there was a moment...

1776
02:20:17,826 --> 02:20:22,240
...when Voldemort's wand and mine
sort of connected.

1777
02:20:23,832 --> 02:20:26,164
<i>Priori Incantatem.</i>

1778
02:20:30,297 --> 02:20:33,004
You saw your parents that night,
didn't you?

1779
02:20:33,592 --> 02:20:35,423
They reappeared.

1780
02:20:36,887 --> 02:20:40,675
No spell can reawaken the dead, Harry.
I trust you know that.

1781
02:20:43,226 --> 02:20:45,842
Dark and difficult times lie ahead.

1782
02:20:46,313 --> 02:20:51,148
Soon we must all face the choice
between what is right and what is easy.

1783
02:20:54,529 --> 02:20:56,190
But remember this:

1784
02:20:56,365 --> 02:20:58,276
You have friends here.

1785
02:21:00,285 --> 02:21:02,025
You're not alone.

1786
02:21:11,213 --> 02:21:13,829
[CHATTERING]

1787
02:21:22,724 --> 02:21:24,464
Hermione.

1788
02:21:24,893 --> 02:21:26,884
This is for you.

1789
02:21:27,479 --> 02:21:29,686
Write to me. Promise.

1790
02:21:30,774 --> 02:21:32,184
Bye.

1791
02:21:38,407 --> 02:21:40,363
<i>Au revoir</i>, Ron.

1792
02:22:04,099 --> 02:22:05,805
[CANNON FIRES]

1793
02:22:07,602 --> 02:22:09,684
[CHEERING]

1794
02:22:24,286 --> 02:22:26,823
Do you think we'll ever just have
a quiet year at Hogwarts?

1795
02:22:26,997 --> 02:22:28,112
-No.
-No.

1796
02:22:28,290 --> 02:22:32,659
No, I didn't think so. Oh, well.
What's life without a few dragons?

1797
02:22:37,090 --> 02:22:39,923
Everything's going to change now,
isn't it?

1798
02:22:47,225 --> 02:22:48,681
Yes.

1799
02:22:53,440 --> 02:22:56,728
Promise you'll write this summer.
Both of you.

1800
02:22:56,902 --> 02:22:59,484
I won't. You know I won't.

1801
02:23:00,739 --> 02:23:03,822
-Harry will, won't you?
-Yeah. Every week.

1802
02:23:03,992 --> 02:23:05,778
[RON AND HARRY CHUCKLE]

1803
02:23:05,952 --> 02:23:08,034
[HORSES WHINNYING]

1804
02:37:01,329 --> 02:37:03,320
[ENGLISH SDH]

